title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in milk, water, eggs and chocolate chips. Mix until well blended and chips are melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes or until set.

title: oatmeal fudgies
directions: Boil together on stove for 1 minute, stirring constantly, sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, stirring until mixed.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Put into refrigerator until cold, then serve and enjoy!

title: marinated fish
directions: Combine juices, oil, sauces and herbs together. Pour over fish and allow to marinate. Bake as desired.

title: lowland supper for low life people
directions: Fill a large 2 to 3 gallon pot halfway with water.
Place seafood pouch in water and bring to a boil.
Put potatoes in and cook for 15 minutes.
Place sausage in and cook for 20 minutes. Place corn in pot and cook for 7 to 10 minutes.
Place shrimp in pot and cook for 3 minutes.
(Use amounts sufficient for number of people you are serving.)

title: coconut delight
directions: Cook pudding in milk; set aside until cold.
Combine flour, butter and pecans.
Pat into a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add pudding, cream cheese mixture and 1 cup of whipped topping and mix.
Pour over crust.
Spread with remaining topping and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: Stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Roll into balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, 40 minutes if balls are frozen.
Makes 50.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and spices.
Mix until blended.
Add apples, shortening and eggs.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer cake pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
The cake does not rise much like a fruit cake.

title: homemade cake frosting
directions: Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Sift sugar, then add the sugar and milk alternately.
Tastes just like bakery icing.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Mix flour and cocoa; set aside.
Beat butter until soft; add sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add egg and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Saving juice, drain cherries and place a cherry into the center of each ball.
In saucepan, combine chocolate chips and milk; heat through until melted.
Add 4 tsp. cherry juice.
Spoon 1 tsp. over each cookie, covering cherry.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat oil with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or tests done.
This bread freezes well.

title: impossible brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread cooked broccoli on plate.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, baking mix, melted oleo and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Top with sliced tomato and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until set (about 30 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vinegar candy
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan; let it cook until threads of hardens when dropped into a little water.
Butter plate and set it to cool, then pull it with a little butter until it is white.
Cut into small pieces with scissors.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugars and milk in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches 228°.
Add butter and pecans and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture just begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased waxed paper; let stand until firm.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Combine flour,	salt and soda.	Add to mixture of eggs, sugar and

Bake in greased muffin
pans at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.	Serve hot. Mixture will keep
six
weeks and you can bake a few at a time for breakfast or a treat.

title: meat and brown gravy
directions: Shape meat into patties and place in a deep baking dish.
Mix both soups together.
Do not add water.
Pour over meat and bake one hour at 350° or until done.
(Cover with lid or foil before baking.)

title: the best chicken pot pie
directions: In large pan, cook chicken, carrots, bay leaf, salt and water.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Cut chicken and all vegetables into bite size pieces.
Remove all fat and skin.
Saut onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, bouillon and pepper; mix well.
Gradually stir in 2 1/2 cups broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in chicken, carrots and peas. Make flaky crust while chicken cooks.

title: cream cake
directions: Whip the two packages of Dream Whip and milk.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar.
Soften cream cheese and blend into Dream Whip mixture.
Slice angel food cake in 1/2-inch pieces.
Put a layer of cake into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of cream cheese mixture over cake pieces.
Repeat with layer of cake and cream cheese mixture.
Top with can of pie filling.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir cheese soup until smooth, gradually adding milk.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternating layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: blessed angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Move oven rack to lowest position.
Mix powdered sugar and flour.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large bowl on medium speed until foamy.
Beat in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add vanilla, almond extract and salt with last addition of sugar.
Continue beating until smooth and glossy. Note:
Do not underbeat.
Sprinkle flour-powdered sugar mixture 1/4 cup at a time over meringue, folding in just until flour-sugar mixture disappears. Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Use knife to cut through batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cracks in cake feel dry and top springs back when touched lightly. Immediately turn pan upside down onto glass bottle or metal funnel.
Leave there until cake is completely cooled.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and retain about 1 tablespoon fat from meat. Drain off the rest.
Shake minced onion in.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer about 1 hour.

title: cherry pie filling
directions: Combine milk and Cool Whip.
Stir in lemon juice.
Mix well. Fold in pie filling and nuts.
Spoon into 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill 2 hours.

title: steak and potatoes casserole
directions: Brown round steak coated in flour.
Put in big casserole dish; coat again with flour.
Pour soup mix and water over steak.
Add sliced carrots and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: steak in sauce
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in shortening.
Pour off excess fat.
Remove steak from pan.
In same pan add margarine and soup.
Stir until blended.
Return steak to pan with sauce and cover.
Cook on low heat until steak is tender, (to your taste), about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: "spanakopita" - spinach pie
directions: Clean and wash spinach; put into a spinner and spin or drain in a colander and allow to drain.
Chop spinach in a large bowl. Chop scallions (white include); add to spinach.
Beat eggs and add to spinach.
Break Feta cheese into small pieces and mix with spinach.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.
Melt butter and mix with olive oil.

Grease a 9 x 13 pan and place six pastry sheets into pan, brushing each sheet with the butter-oil mixture. Spread spinach mixture, then place 6 additional sheets on top, brushing each sheet with the butter-oil mixture.
With a sharp knife, cut through the top 6 sheets in three places.
Spread oil-butter mixture on top of last sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 50 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.
Serves 15.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Layer One:
Mix together
flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: shorty's spicy deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil the eggs; cool, peel and cut in half.
Place yolks in mixing bowl and chop into extremely fine pieces (the finer the pieces the smoother it will be).

Add onion salt (approximately 1/2 teaspoon), Worcestershire sauce (approximately 1 teaspoon) and mayonnaise and horseradish sauce (the mayo and horseradish sauce should be 2 parts mayo to 1 part horseradish).
Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Add mixture to cut egg halves by using an icing bag.
Sprinkle top of eggs lightly with paprika.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, cranberries and drained pineapple while hot.
Pour and mold; refrigerate.
Makes 2 medium size molds or 1 large mold.

title: crabmeat-cheese dip
directions: Brown onion; add cheese and melt.
Add seasonings; stir in crabmeat and salad dressing (mayo).
Serve warm over fondue flame or bake about 30 minutes at 350° in casserole dish.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas chicken gumbo
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes.
Remove chicken. Brown sausage, cut into slices.
Add tomatoes, onion and sausage to broth.
Simmer 10 minutes or until okra is tender.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wrap one or two strips of bacon around each breast.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup and pour over breasts.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes finely.
Chop peppers.
Chop garlic buds finely. Combine all ingredients and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve with chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 cube butter together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Don't bake.

title: shortcut chili sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over tomato mixture.
Boil for 30 to 40 minutes. Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 8 half-pints.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir boiling water into gelatin 2 minutes or until dissolved.
In a separate bowl, mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened. Remove any remaining ice.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Use 2-quart saucepan.

Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, orange rind and milk; cook to soft ball stage, 230°, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; add vanilla and walnuts and stir until grainy. Turn out at once onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Separate nuts while still warm.
Store in jars.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix
first
ingredients
like pie crust.
Add enough milk to	make a soft dough.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick and cover with apple slices.	Roll like jelly roll.
Slice 1-inch pieces and put
in a 9 x 13-inch pan.	Make a syrup of next
4 ingredients. Pour over cake in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes(for our little "deers")
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; mixing until well blended.
Add egg, mix well and spread into bottom of pie shell.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Place drained sausage in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle pepper, onion and cheese on top of sausage.
Slightly beat eggs in medium mixing bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over mixture in crust.
Sprinkle paprika on top if desired, also a little red sweet pepper makes it more attractive.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: roses' baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter or margarine and stir in the flour over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until roux is lightly browned.
Remove from heat and stir in the tomatoes, onion, egg, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over the macaroni.
Stir and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and set aside. Dice chicken.
Saute in butter or oleo. Add celery, onion and parsley. Saute until vegetables are clear.
Add contents of package of noodles and sauce. Add water. Cook for about 14 minutes or until noodles are tender. Serves 4.

title: chocolate melt-aways
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in Bits and nuts.
Using a rounded teaspoonful, shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: floppy rolls
directions: Flop rolls into melted butter, then flop into cinnamon and sugar mixture and then flop into a baking pan.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice with powdered sugar icing. Eat.

title: glass cleaner(not to eat)
directions: Put all into quart jar and fill with water.
Mix and pour into empty spray bottle.
"Works really good!"

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend for 1 minute at high speed. Pour into greased and floured 10 inch pyrex pie dish. Bake at 325 for 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Drain liquid from cherries into saucepan.
Add sugar and boil liquid and sugar for 1 minute.
Set off heat.
Add gelatine, cherries, juices and rind.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken burgers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix all ingredients, except buns. Fill buns with chicken mixture.
Wrap each sandwich in square of foil; place on baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until hot. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Then add eggs.
Sift together salt, baking powder and flour.
Fold into butter and sugar mixture; add vanilla.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out dough about 1/8-inch and cut into cookies.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans in water; season with salt and bacon drippings. Add sausage and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add onion, celery, garlic and bay leaf.
Cook over low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add heated water, if needed.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Select fresh cucumbers and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over sticks and let stand 12 to 14 hours or overnight. Drain and pack into jars.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers in jar.
Process in water bath for 5 minutes for pints or 10 minutes for quarts.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened margarine or butter with sugars and eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add to batter, blend well.
Drop cookies from a teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes, makes about 8 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini in 1/2 cup boiling water 10 minutes.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in carrots a few minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a tube pan.

title: chicken and zucchini stir-fry
directions: Coat large skillet with cooking oil.
Add chicken and garlic. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly.
When the chicken turns white, add soy sauce and continue stirring several minutes.
Add vegetables and cook a few minutes more.
Add cornstarch
paste and stir for about 1 minute more.
Garnish with almonds.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: fish italiano
directions: Pour butter into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange onion evenly in bottom of dish.
Place fish in single layer, atop onion.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and salt.
Spread evenly over fish.
Sprinkle oregano and parsley over top to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chipped ham sloppy joes
directions: Mix, heat and serve.

title: chocolate ice box pie
directions: Pour into two 8-inch graham cracker pie shells and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: quick corn relish
directions: In a small sauce pan combine reserved corn liquid, onion, green pepper, pimento, vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed, and red pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in corn.
Cool and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: white lily "light" biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Measure flour into bowl.
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 20 strokes.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart for crusty biscuits or almost touching for soft sides.
Bake at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: barbecue glazed drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Coat an 8-inch square baking dish. In a medium saucepan, combine the vinegar, mustard, sugar, butter, soy sauce, red pepper and black pepper. Stir well. Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil, allowing it to boil for 5 minutes to thicken, stirring constantly. Place drumsticks in the baking pan and pour sauce mixture over them, coating completely. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dijon country chicken
directions: Cut refrigerator leftovers into cubes and arrange on large platter.
Put dip types into cups with small spoons or knife, then with cupboard leftovers arrange them around the outside edge of platter.
Serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease off.
Add soup, ketchup and mustard; stir.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 16.

title: orange chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Beat egg yolks.
Add salt, orange and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and orange rind.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until thick.
Add rest of sugar (1/2 cup).
Pour filling into graham cracker crust.
Cover with meringue.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix ingredients well, then chill.
Spread 1/2 bottle chili sauce over mixture after chilled.
Top with 2 cans crabmeat. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Saute onions in salad oil.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, dry mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and catsup. Heat to boiling.
Pour mixture over butter beans in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crawfish or shrimp fettuccini
directions: Boil noodles and sit them aside.
Saut onions, peppers, celery and green onions with margarine until soft.
Add flour, parsley and crawfish or shrimp.
Cook about 15 minutes on low fire.
Add Velveeta and half and half.
Stir until Velveeta is melted.
Remove from fire.	Add noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bavarian dessert
directions: In top of double boiler, combine gelatin, salt and sugar (first 3 ingredients).
Stir in egg yolks.
Then slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until mixture coats spoon.
Remove and refrigerate until like unbeaten egg whites.

title: chicken royalle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions; drain and add chicken and soup.
Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into a casserole dish; sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese, then the Mozzarella cheese and onion on top of cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Cut beef (round steak or cubed steak) into thin strips. Stir-fry 10 minutes in oil. Add onion, garlic, tomato, green pepper and spices.
Add cabbage, cut in wedges.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with baked potatoes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook peas in water until drained.
Fry bacon until crisp. Drain.
Layer lettuce, peas, celery and green pepper in bowl. Combine mayo and sugar.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Chill overnight.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: On low heat, melt chocolate.
Blend in vanilla and sugar. Dissolve sugar.
Put in peanut butter.
Then add oatmeal.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cream 1 cup sugar with cream cheese and add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in water and stir in strawberries.
Let set partially, then pour over cheese mixture and chill until firm. (Pretzels taste as if crust is made of nuts.)

title: saffron rice
directions: In saucepan, heat broth with saffron until hot.
Set aside. Saute onion until tender in 2 tablespoons of butter about 2 minutes.
Add rice and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, about 5 minutes.
Add reserved broth, 1/2 cup of water and wine; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Before serving, add more butter (2 tablespoons) and cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked turkey hash casserole
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onion in oil until tender only. Add milk and seasonings; drain mushrooms and blend 1/2 cup mushroom liquid with flour.
Pour gradually into frying pan and stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Add turkey.
Pour into casserole and arrange mushrooms on top.
Put into hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes, until thoroughly hot.
Do not overcook celery and green pepper, as these are added texture needed.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes. Strain.
Make white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Just before serving, slowly add hot, strained tomatoes to white sauce, stirring constantly. Do not reheat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, peanut butter, water and egg; stir by hand until dough forms.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on flat pan.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven immediately; top each cookie with Hershey's Kiss in center.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: maple french toast bake
directions: Arrange half of the bread cubes in a 2 quart pan. Top with cream cheese cubes, then add remaining bread cubes. In a bowl, whisk eggs, milk and syrup. Pour over bread cubes. Refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 20 to 25 minutes longer, or until golden brown. Serve with additional syrup.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, eggs, margarine and shortening until fluffy.
Blend in lemon extract.
Add flour and milk, alternately beating after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Allow to cool before serving.
Serve plain, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or top with your favorite glaze.

title: brisket with green chili
directions: Place brisket in baking dish. Add ingredients and top with green chili. Cook in 250° oven for about 5 to 6 hours or until tender. Slice and enjoy.

title: grandma's teacakes
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mix alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and zest.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: meat casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt to taste.
Mince 1 onion and spread over meat.
Mix soups and pour over onion and meat.
Do not add water to soup!
Put Tater Tots over soup.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
The last 15 minutes, you may have to cover if Tater Tots look too brown.
May freeze what is left.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until soft.
Slowly add sugar.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375° for 1/2 hour.
Put the cookies in the oven.
Turn off heat; let remain in there for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open the door.
This should make approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add drained pineapple, strawberries, nuts and bananas. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners in four pieces and wrap with bacon.
(Cut bacon into pieces that will fit around wieners.)
Put toothpick through wieners and bacon to hold together.
Cook in slow cooker with brown sugar until it is cooked down low or about three hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour half of mixture in bowl and congeal.
When firm, add topping and other half of Jell-O.

title: school day casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: chicken grape salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon coconut topping
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Spread over doughnuts and sprinkle with shredded coconut.

title: marinated veggies
directions: *Cucumbers, zucchini, green beans, broccoli, cauliflower, green onions, carrots, green pepper, red pepper or sliced water chestnuts (no radishes) may be used.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In a large bowl combine 3 cups flour, yeast, salt and soda. Stir in lemon rind.
In a saucepan combine water, milk and honey. Heat to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients and beat well.
Add remaining flour to stiffen batter.
Spoon into small well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Allow to rise to top of dish. Microwave on High 6 1/2 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken in lemon sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add other ingredients, except chicken; cook until onion is clear.
Cut chicken into pieces; arrange in a large, shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken; let marinate for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
Baste often; dust with paprika.
Serve with rice cooked with beef bouillon cube.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend together soup and flour; add sour cream, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and turn in 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and butter. Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: deep delta shrimp
directions: Saute flour until golden; add green pepper, celery and garlic; saute until tender.
Add seasonings, tomato paste and water.
Cook stirring until thick.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add shrimp before serving, enough to heat.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Put 1/3 of this into baking dish. Pour 1 can of oysters with juice over crackers.
Pepper; repeat layers.
Pour milk over top.
Let stand for about 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Cool.
Crumble in large pieces.
Pour ingredients over crumbs and layer like banana pudding.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deep fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Mix egg and water together. Dip chicken in egg mixture and roll in crumbs.
Put in deep fryer in hot grease, 350° to 375°, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: extra creamy fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all sugar and cocoa.
Set aside.
In saucepan, mix margarine, cheese and vanilla.
Melt on low heat.
Pour mixture in bowl with sugar and cocoa.
Mix well. Add pecans.
Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut in squares.
Serve.

title: arnold's 3 day sun dills
directions: Place a layer of dill on the bottom of the jar.
Add a layer of pickles.
Alternate 2 more layers of pickles and dill.
Mix and heat remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over pickles and dill. Close the jar and set in the sun for 3 days.

title: hot lemon sauce
directions: Combine, then mix thoroughly, the sugar and cornstarch.
Add slowly the boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add, then blend well, the lemon juice, lemon rind, butter, salt and vanilla.
Serve hot.
Great on gingerbread.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix undrained strawberries, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into strawberry mixture, reserving about 1/2 cup flour.
Stir to blend.
Stir nuts into reserved flour (this keeps nuts from sinking to the bottom) and add to bread mixture; stir well.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine milk and oil.
Add to dry mix.
Stir until moistened.
Drop from tablespoon into bubbly broth.
Cover tightly.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown.
Mix all ingredients in baking pan, except cheese.
Bake in oven until potatoes are soft. Add cheese to top and brown.

title: artichoke fritters
directions: Heat 2 1/2-inches oil. In a medium bowl, combine next 5 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine flour, cheese, baking powder, salt and garlic.
Add dry ingredients to artichoke mixture. Mix well.

title: apple surprise cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: sugar-free applesauce cake
directions: Combine and cook raisins in water until water is absorbed. Cool.
Combine eggs, applesauce, oil, vanilla and Sugar Twin. Sift flour, soda and spices.
Add to egg mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan or flat baking pan (batter will be thin).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to butter, sugar and egg mixture, alternating with milk, until well blended.
If dough is sticky, add flour to handle.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on well floured pastry cloth or wax paper.
Using well floured cookie cutters, cut out desired shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place bake-on decorations and bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Makes about 100 cookies.

title: sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, shortening, cocoa and water and bring to boil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.
Then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a cookie sheet.

title: baked bean brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: violet petal jelly
directions: Fill a quart jar with violet blossoms, without any stems. Cover with boiling water.
Seal with a cover and let stand one day. Strain; save infusion and discard flowers.
To 2 cups of infusion, add lemon juice (lovely change of color) and pectin.
Bring mixture just to a boil.
Add sugar; return to boil and boil for 1 minute. Fill canning jars, leaving 1/8-inch on top.
Proceed as you do with any jello recipe.

title: oven french toast
directions: Heat Karo, brown sugar and butter; pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat together eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Put 1st mixture in pan. Place bread, stacked 3 slices high in pan.
Pour 2nd mixture over all.
Cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes covered and 20 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, eggs and vanilla. Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: butterscotch bars(no bake)
directions: In a saucepan, beat and cook eggs, sugar and oleo.
Pour over the first four ingredients.
Mix well, but gently.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with last 2 ingredients that have been melted over low heat.
Let sit until top is firm.
Cut in squares.

title: buttermilk shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender just long enough to blend. Makes 2 cups.
Tastes just like a "liquid cheesecake".

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cool.
Drain vegetables.
Chop eggs and mix all ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cabbage and lima beans
directions: Rinse sauerkraut thoroughly; drain in colander.
Shred cabbage; combine with sauerkraut.
Cover with cold water; cook 1 hour.
In a frypan, lightly brown flour; add enough warm water to make a thin sauce.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Add lima beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Add oats to next 9 ingredients and beat together until well mixed. Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven.
Boil oleo, brown sugar, milk and vanilla for 3 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread over hot cake.
Return to broiler until lightly browned.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Mix molasses and mustard; stir in vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 3 cups.

title: marmaduke's favorite cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add this mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill overnight.

title: cowboy stew
directions: In a 5 to 6 quart pan, add all ingredients and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add water, if needed.

title: frozen cheese cake
directions: In a small bowl beat egg whites, then beat the whipping cream. Put them together in a large mixing bowl; mix egg yolks, sugar, salt, vanilla and cream cheese in bowl and beat until smooth. Fold in egg whites and cream.
Pour in 9-inch pie crust and freeze.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
If glass, bake at 350°.

title: apple crunch
directions: Fill a casserole 3/4 full of sliced apples; sprinkle a handful of granulated sugar over the apples.
Mix brown sugar, butter and oatmeal together.
Place over apples.
Bake at 350 - 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple-pumpkin chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray nonstick baking sheet with cooking spray.
Wash and core, but do not peel, the apples. Grate apples into a medium sized bowl (this should make about 2 cups).
Add pumpkin, molasses, sugar, lemon zest and vanilla. Stir to combine.
Set aside.

title: christopher jollief's peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 baking sheets; keep warm.
Combine soda, 1 teaspoon water and the vanilla; set aside.
Combine sugar, 1 cup water and the corn syrup in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 240° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of syrup dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball, which flattens when removed from water).
Stir in butter and peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly until thermometer reaches 300° (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into threads, which are hard and brittle).
Watch carefully so the mixture doesn't burn.
Immediately remove from heat.
Stir in soda mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: strawberry cream gelatin salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together water and gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes or until semi-firm.
Set remaining gelatin mixture aside at room temperature.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Blend together to make loaf.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add parsley flakes before serving.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions for 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cool on wire rack.
Drain cherries, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Sprinkle over 1 cake layer. Spread with pie filling.
Place remaining layer on top.
Spread whipped cream over top and sides of cake.
Decorate with cherries and chocolate curls.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: russian cream from my sister alice
directions: In a small pan, blend together the sugar and unflavored gelatin.
Add water and
mix well.	Let stand about 5 minutes, then bring to
a
full
rolling
boil, stirring.
Remove sugar mixture from heat and pour	in
the cream.	In a bowl, mix the sour cream with
vanilla, then gradually, smoothly beat in the hot sugar mixture.
Pour
into	casserole
dish
and cover and chill until set.	(At
least 4 hours or as long as overnight.) Serve the cream with the fruit.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ovenproof dish.
Pour cake mix over melted butter.
Pour fruit over cake mix.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bakes
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt, oleo and cocoa in pan. Bring to a rolling boil for 1 full minute. Remove from heat. Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick. Drop by small teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: shrimp cracker spread
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayo and onion.
Mix together eggs and shrimp.
Put 1/2 cream cheese mixture in bottom of a buttered dish.
Top with 1/2 shrimp and egg mixture.
Repeat layers; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Must keep warm.

title: mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Mash cooked potatoes until smooth.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Add coconut and raisins.
Spread evenly in baking dish and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add marshmallows to top.
Bake until brown.
Serve.

title: superior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Shape into loaf; put in loaf pan.
Pour a can of meat loaf fixings over loaf.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrots with nutmeg
directions: Cut carrots in large chunks, approximately 1 1/2 to 2-inches long.
Carrots seem much more flavorful when prepared in larger pieces.
Put the water, salt, sugar, nutmeg and butter in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan with lid.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots; cover and reduce heat to medium.
Simmer approximately 12 to 15 minutes, depending on the thickness of the carrots, until tender.
Remove with a slotted spoon to a preheated serving dish.
Save carrot broth for soup stock.

title: italian sausage
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Stuff in casing or make patties.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (with hands).
Roll into balls and bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: cranberry and orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Cut orange in wedges and remove seeds.
Put orange and cranberries through food grinder.
Mix in apple and sugar.
Fold into thickened gelatin.
Pour into individual molds or in any dish desired.

title: my favorite chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crust.
Mix pie crust according to directions on package.
Roll out into 1-inch strips. Line 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with half of the pie crust strips. Pour chicken mixture into casserole dish.
Top with remaining half of pie crust strips.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 minutes or until crust is brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carolyn's lasagna
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add lasagna noodles to boiling salted water and cook for 20 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat together
shortening
and 1 cup of the sugar until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Sift
dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to sugar mix, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and lemon rind.

title: irish potato bread
directions: Combine all ingredients with a little milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes with a small round cutter.
Cook on both sides on a hot plate or griddle until brown.
Serve with lashings of butter, bacon and eggs.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix together like pie crust the shortening, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add, after mixing together, egg, anise seed, vanilla, soda and buttermilk.
Add more flour so able to handle, similar to pie dough.
Roll on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: In a bowl cream together butter, sugar and eggs with a mixer. Fold in the remaining ingredients; and pour in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel pecan cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
Bake as directed. When cake is done (while hot), punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over.
When cake is completely cool, ice with caramel pecan icing.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: In a large, heavy saucepot, heat oil over medium-high heat; add beef and brown all sides.
Remove and set aside.
In same pot, over medium heat, cook onions 3 minutes, or until tender.
Return meat to pot; add tomatoes, barley, water, soy sauce, thyme and salt.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery, beans and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ham and cheese biscuit bake
directions: Combine Bisquick, oil and milk; beat until stiff.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over dough.
Place ham slices over dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices on top and return to oven until cheese bubbles.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add sour milk alternately with flour mixture, beating after each addition.
Gently fold in berries.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) round cake pans that have been prepared with wax paper on the bottom of pans and greased and floured around sides.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: reeses candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; beat well.
Roll into balls; refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: cheese danish
directions: Press out first can refrigerated crescent rolls in slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Press seams together.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread on top of crust. Spread out second can of crescent rolls on top of mixture, pressing seams together. Melt margarine, pour over top.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this for top.
Pat remaining crumbs into ungreased pan.
Top that layer with peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread evenly.
Crumble remaining ingredients over this.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed of an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add butter, sugar, coconut, flour and pineapple. Mix well.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer slowly for several hours.

title: king bars
directions: Mix well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: souffle of spinach
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: torta
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain and set aside.
Cook onion and hash browns together in oil until tender.
Add meat back to pan and mix together well.
In separate pan, scramble eggs, then add to meat mixture.
Season with soy sauce and garlic powder to taste.
Serve with rice.

title: nachos
directions: Slice cheese and put in microwave-safe bowl.
Pour the milk in with the cheese.
Put in the microwave for 1 minute.
Stir.
Put in an additional mixture. Stir.
Spread chips on plate.
Put as much cheese, chili and anything else you desire on top of the chips.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Boil together the margarine, sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut; pour over cake while cake is still warm.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut, and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.

title: towitier pie(french canadian)
directions: Put meat in a
saucepan.
Add
water, spices and onion. Cook for 1 hour
over
moderate
heat, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add potatoes.
Mix well and cool.

title: salsa with fresh cilantro
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips or Mexican foods.
Great in guacamole.

title: grandma's favorite lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In heavy saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups sugar and cornstarch. Add lemon juice. In small bowl, beat egg yolks and add to lemon mixture. Gradually add water, stirring constantly. Over medium heat, cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Add margarine; stir until melted. Pour into baked crust.

title: basic recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over slow heat.
This mixture can be used for chili, enchiladas, pizza or mixed in macaroni, poured over rice, or anything else you might want.
If you don't brown the meat, the mixture could be used for meat loaf.

title: tabbouli salad
directions: Pour boiling water over wheat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain well in colander.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: spicy mexican corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish with margarine.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Shape in 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from sheet.

title: challah
directions: Combine warm water, dry yeast and 2 teaspoons honey.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes, then add 3 eggs and 1 egg white (reserve yolk for crust).
Add oil, salt, 1 teaspoon honey and flour.
Beat well as you add flour until stiff, then knead and let rise in oiled, covered bowl until double.
Punch down.
Separate and roll into 3 coils.
Start off by pinching the ends together and braid as you would hair.
Place on greased cookie sheet and cover with a towel. Let rise until double in size.
Brush with egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: grilled chops(low calorie)
directions: Place chops in a Ziploc bag.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix and pour into bag over chops.
Press out all air; seal bag.
Let marinate 4 hours in refrigerator.
Lift chops from bag and broil or barbecue.
Brush with marinade occasionally.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes on each side.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbled sausage. Top with shredded cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour mixture over
cheese. Chill at least 8 hours or overnight. Bake 40 minutes at 350° for a souffl breakfast.

title: turkey cookies
directions: You also need 1 plastic knife and 1 napkin.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a buttered shallow baking dish, arrange the asparagus in a layer. Slice hard-cooked eggs in layer over asparagus. Pour the chicken soup, diluted with the water, over all. Sprinkle bread crumbs, butter and cheese over all. Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown.

title: baked parmesan perch
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, paprika and basil.
Brush fish fillets with butter, then dip into crumb mixture.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 500° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Yield: 4 servings.

title: mom's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Add shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Add beef and onions, saving some to put on top.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Soak rabbit overnight in salted water.
Cook and bone rabbit. Combine peas, carrots and potatoes in large dish.
Add rabbit, salt and pepper.
Roll dough in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and cover with dough.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses together.
Stir baking soda, flour, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: herb mayonnaise
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise (or salad dressing), mustard, lemon juice and tarragon; cover and refrigerate.
Can be stored for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 3/4 cup sauce.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn and put in paper bag. Boil the remaining ingredients 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix syrup into popcorn.
Pack as high as you can onto cookie sheets. Bake in a 200° oven for 2 hours.
Let cool and break into chunks and put into containers.

title: cashew gravy
directions: Blend
all
ingredients
until
creamy.
Add 1 1/2 cups more water.
Blend.
Cook over low to medium heat until thick. Serve with patties or loaf.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: batter bread
directions: Mix sugar, yeast and warm water.
Whip eggs in separate bowl. Add salt, flour and oatmeal to yeast mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix well, then add oleo to batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Let rise 1 hour, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: flavor craver shrimp dip
directions: In bowl, soften cream cheese.
Blend in chili sauce until smooth.
Mix in salad dressing, onion and horseradish.
Fold in tiny shrimp.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Add while hot the remaining ingredients.
Stir 5 minutes or until thick enough to spoon out on sheet of waxed paper.
Spoon out the size of cookies desired.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed, one at a time.
Chill 20 minutes. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet 4 inches apart.
Make only 1 at a time.
Spread very thin with back of spoon to 3 inches in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack. Working quickly, place fortune in center of cookie.
Fold in half. Grasp rounded edges between thumb and forefinger of one hand. Place forefinger of the other hand at center of folded edge; push in.
Bring edges of fold downward around forefinger.
Place in muffin tin; open edges up until set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate lumpies
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar. Add to melted chocolate.
Mix together egg, half and half and vanilla, and add to chocolate/sugar mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder and mix into dough.
Add walnuts to mixture and mix well.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet (won't spread) and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato in the skin until tender.
Cool.
Peel and mash well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Add sugar (more if necessary) until mixture is the consistency of pie dough. Divide dough into 4 to 5 parts.
Put dough on wax paper or a pastry cloth that has been covered with confectioners sugar.
Roll out thin like a pie crust and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: norma's emergency casserole
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion in olive oil until lightly brown.
Slowly add 1 can tomato soup and 1 tablespoon of steak sauce.
Cook 3 ounces of wide noodles until just tender.
Mix with browned beef and the juice of a small can of English peas.
Add small amount of oleo to peas.
Place in small casserole.
Top with peas, then top with grated mild Cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour on 300°.
The foil keeps cheese from burning. Remove foil the last several minutes of cooking.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Arrange pieces in single layer in baking dish.
Pour dressing over chicken so all sides are coated. Let stand all day or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain dressing in bowl and thoroughly mix with apricot preserves.
Brush (or spoon) mixture over each piece of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for about 1 hour or until tender and glazed.

title: sweet potato pecan casserole
directions: In large bowl let egg whites warm to room temperature about 1 hour, also preheat oven to 375°.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites with salt just until peaks form when beater is slowly raised.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
In another large bowl, using same beater, combine sweet potatoes, 1/4 cup sugar, egg yolk, cinnamon, mace and orange peel.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, until mixture is smooth. Meanwhile in small saucepan, heat cream to boiling.
Slowly add to sweet potato mixture, beating until combined.
With wire whisk, using an under and over motion, fold sweet potato mixture and pecans into egg whites just until combined.
Gently turn into 1-quart straight sided souffle dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
(Ten minutes before end of baking time, arrange whole pecans on top.)
Serve at once, with butter.

title: norwegian holiday bread
directions: Heat the butter and milk to melt butter.

Cool to lukewarm. Soften the yeast in the warm water. Stir in sugar, salt, raisins, cherries, almonds, egg and the milk mixture. Gradually add the flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. Let rise, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add slightly beaten egg and molasses. Mix dry ingredients together; add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Dough will be loose.
Take less than teaspoonful and shape with knife.
Bake in 375° oven approximately 15 to 18 minutes.

title: seasoned flour for chicken
directions: Place in plastic bag and shake to mix.
Place moistened chicken pieces into bag and shake.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add egg and onion.
Add enough milk so mixture will drop easily from spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil.
Cook until brown, turning once.

title: cranberry walnut french toast
directions: Mix together and soak bread for at least one hour.
Pan saut until golden, then finish in oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
This can be done the night before and just finished in oven before serving.

title: onion rolls
directions: Roll biscuits to 3 x 5-inches.
Saute onions in butter until onions are clear.
Place 1 to 2 teaspoons onions and 1 tablespoon cheese on rolled out biscuits.
Roll up tight.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake until golden brown.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes or longer.

title: grandma serene's meatballs
directions: In a bowl, mix hamburger meat, salt, pepper, eggs and ketchup. Put in two pieces of white bread (torn into little pieces) and 1 grated onion.
Mix everything well.

title: pretzel salad(one-half is plenty for most families.)
directions: Note:
This salad is in three layers.

title: lemon rice
directions: Mix all ingredients to chicken broth, except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in 2 teaspoons parsley.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook shrimp in 1-quart water with 4 peppercorns for 3 minutes. Saute green peppers, celery, onions and garlic in cooking oil; add other ingredients (except shrimp) and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cooperation
directions: Start with a mixture of children; add loving and giving parents.
Blend with caring teachers to form a batch of Cooperation.
Serve frequently.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and	pack lightly in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt and pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Serve with sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cajun squash
directions: Steam zucchini and yellow squash in pot of boiling water until tender; drain, set aside and keep warm.
In 5-quart pan, melt butter over high heat.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic and andouille.
Saute until onion is wilted (5 to 7 minutes).
Add ground beef; blend well until beef is well browned, about 30 minutes.
Season well with salt and cayenne pepper.
Add squash and mix.
Bring to a slight simmer; cook about 20 minutes.
Adjust seasonings and remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs; mix well and place in a casserole dish or large baking pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Serves 12 to 15.
Cut in half for home use.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as per instructions.
Combine soup, cream cheese, cheddar cheese and mix with vegetables.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Put mushrooms on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6-8

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(mama's)
directions: Heat pumpkin and take off heat.
Blend in flour, Eagle Brand milk, salt, brown sugar, vanilla and butter.
Set aside.
Beat together 1/2 cup sugar and spices.
Add eggs to sugar-spice mixture.
Mix together sugar-spice mixture and pumpkin mixture. Pour in enough milk to make about 3 quarts of filling.
Makes 2 large pies and 1 small pie.
Bake at 425° until starts cooking good, and turn back to 400° until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips over double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add condensed milk, vanilla and peanuts.
Mix and drop by teaspoon onto a buttered cookie sheet or on wax paper.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: berry-poppy seed salad
directions: Combine oil, honey, vinegar, poppy seed and mustard in bowl and mix well.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce, berries and onion. Toss with dressing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw, but do not cook, the broccoli. Mix with onion, cottage cheese, eggs, oil, salt and muffin mix. Pour in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve hot, cut into squares. Freezes well.

title: squash pie
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set and brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Pour melted margarine in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chutney
directions: Place all ingredients into 6-quart pot and mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and place in hot glass jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in pan and pour water on them and salt.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and sprinkle over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and pineapple.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bring to boil and cook 12 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into glasses and top with hot wax.
Makes 8 glasses.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together the vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over the vegetables.
This will keep 6 weeks in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cereal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add rest of ingredients.
Drop ingredients by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl with spoon or spatula. DO NOT use mixer. Refrigerate.

title: deep fried chicken wings
directions: Clean chicken wings.
Drop in hot cooking oil and cook until done.
Put seasoning in bag add wings and shake.
Serve.

title: boxmans rolls(heritage recipe)
directions: Heat milk, add butter, sugar and salt.
In small portion of milk dissolve yeast.
Beat eggs.
add flour, eggs, etc.
Mix well. Let rise.
Then shape into rolls and let rise again and bake.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, bell pepper and onions; soak for 3 hours with 1/2 cup salt.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Drain cucumbers and add to
liquid
mixture.
Bring
to a boil, but do not boil.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: christmas stollen(weihnachts-oder sachrischer)
directions: Prepare a firm dough of flour, milk, yeast, salt, sugar and lard.
Work until in blisters.
Knead in raisins, grated almonds and orange peel.
Cover dough and let rise to double in size. Sprinkle bread board with flour and roll dough out.
Make into loaves.
Brush with melted lard or butter.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in 375° oven until bread leaves sides of pan, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Leave in oven for 10 minutes after turning off.

title: creamy lemonade pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding mix, beat on low speed of mixer for 2 minutes, mixture will be thick. In another bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Gradually beat in lemonade concentrate. Gradually beat in pudding mixture. Pour into crust. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: country style steak
directions: Mix
flour,
salt
and	pepper.
Dip steaks in mixture. Heat oil
in
large
skillet
or iron frying pan; brown steaks quickly. Remove
steaks
from pan and remove all but 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add
2 to 3 tablespoons flour and brown.
Add approximately 2 cups cold water slowly.
Cook until smooth and slightly
thick. Return
steaks
to	gravy.	Add
the onions; cover and cook slowly for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-olive cocktail snack
directions: Combine all ingredients except olives.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Mold mixture around each olive.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Yields 25 servings.

title: bill's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut.
For soft cookies, use 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup shortening, instead of 1 cup butter and roll thick.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix together powdered milk, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in warm water just until dough clings together. Knead dough until it is soft, not sticky. Cover and let stand for 2 hours. Shape into 2 inch balls; flatten by patting with hands until you have a circle about 8 inches. Make a small hole in center. Fry in about 1/2 inch of shortening. Bread should be light brown on each side. Use tongs to turn.
Drain on paper towels. Can be topped with powdered sugar or honey.

title: german style beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Combine all ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in a saucepan, stirring constantly (medium heat).
Boil for 10 to 15 seconds, continuing to stir.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat until thickening begins.
Spread quickly on lukewarm cake.
Good on chocolate cake.

title: silverado taco casserole
directions: Place 1/2 taco shells in lightly greased baking dish.
Brown beef; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water.
Simmer.
Add onion and tomato sauce.
Spoon meat mixture over 1/2 shells.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Sprinkle remaining shells and rest of cheese. Top with tomato wedges and green olive slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli in large plastic bowl. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth and creamy. Pour over broccoli. Add onions, bacon and cheese. Cover bowl with lid and shake until all mixed. Top with sunflower seeds.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain fat. Add salt and pepper.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Add enough water to hold together. Roll thin and cut into small squares. Drop into hot grease. Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon or with honey.

title: florentine salad
directions: Wash and stem spinach.
Slice mushrooms and combine with spinach.
Chill. Combine remaining ingredients except eggs and chill.
After 3 hours, remove garlic from dressing and pour over the salad and mix.
Sprinkle eggs on top.
Bacon bits may also be sprinkled on top.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In a 4 or 5-quart glass or ceramic dish (must be this size or mixture will boil over), stir together buttermilk, sugar, pecans, salt, butter and vanilla.
Cook on High for 12 minutes, stirring at 4 minute intervals.
Stir in baking soda.
Mixture will become foamy.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Beat mixture until tacky (about 2 minutes).
Drop by teaspoons on a sheet of foil.
Pralines will become hard in a few minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Remove; put aside.
Cook onion in small amount of water until soft (in same frying pan). Add soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until mixed. Simmer 40 to 60 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chops just before ready to serve.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and some flour.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator overnight.
About 2 hours before baking, shape into rolls (knots, etc.) and place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until light.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: italian style baked chicken
directions: Mix together salt, pepper, rosemary and garlic.
Set aside. Melt shortening and margarine in pan.
Add wine to strained tomatoes in a bowl.
Marinate the chicken in bowl with dry seasonings and melted shortening and margarine.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
When baking lay the chicken in roasting pan with skins up and baste with tomato, wine sauce.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven or until skin is brown.
Serves 6.

title: baked spinach country style
directions: Cook spinach in boiling, salted water until tender; drain thoroughly in sieve.
Meanwhile, cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in flour, then milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in spinach.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss cracker crumbs with melted butter, then cheese.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans and new potatoes
directions: Place salt pork and water in a large Dutch oven; cover and cook over medium heat 1 hour. Add green beans, onion, and pepper; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add potatoes; cover and simmer 50 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Make sauce and boil lasagna noodles.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Run cool water over noodles.
Put in layers in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese and end with sauce and cheese on top to melt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit a few minutes. Cut in squares with square spatula.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in round slices.
Fry sausage. Crumble and drain.
In a baking dish layer potatoes, sausage and soup until you've used it all.
Then put cheese on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and pour white vinegar over.
Let stand 1 hour, drain again.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and top with dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add rice, mushroom soup and Cheez-Whiz.
Cook frozen broccoli, then add cheese mixture.
Bake in casserole 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Dissolve Hershey bars and marshmallows in the milk, but do not let mixture boil. Cool and gel in refrigerator. Add the whipped cream to gelled chocolate mixture. Pour into baked pie crust. Return to refrigerator and cool.

title: take along baked beans
directions: Cook bacon, onion rings and green pepper until tender; drain. Combine all ingredients in a 2 qt. casserole.

title: tops style chili
directions: Cook ground meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: crach-top cookies
directions: Mix together Crisco, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, white sugar, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix well and make into small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Easy to make.

title: wheat bread(for bread makers)
directions: Put into bread pan in this order.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper to drain.
In same pan, saute onions and potatoes until browned.
Pour eggs into skillet; cook and stir gently until eggs are set and cooked until desired doneness.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon; let stand until cheese is melted.

title: mint chocolate chip shake(yield: two 8 oz. drinks)
directions: 1. Put 2 large scoops of Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream into a blender.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic in meat drippings.
Add paste; stir. Add tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to boil. Lower heat.
Add more meat drippings, if needed.
Simmer on low heat for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Can be placed in oven in pan for same amount of time at 350°.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: Put tomato juice, sugar, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir.
Let foam settle down and add milk slowly.
Add butter and serve.

title: chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chews are done when the middle rises and falls back down.
Cool before cutting.

title: summer apple salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine apples, pineapple, celery, grapes, carrot and almonds.
In a small bowl combine sour cream, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Add apple mixture and toss to coat.
Chill.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in hot water according to package directions. When grits are cooked, add margarine and cheese.
Cook slowly until melted. Remove from heat and add remainder of ingredients. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 hour at 250°, uncovered. Serves 8.

title: lemonade
directions: Soften lemons.
Cut off one end of each lemon and gouge with knife to loosen pulp.
Squeeze the juice into the pitcher and slice lemon.
Add sugar.
Pour hot tap water over sugar, lemon slices and juice.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove lemon slices and seeds.
Fill pitcher with cold water to make 2 quarts.
Serve over ice.

title: marriage stew(2 full servings)
directions: With the ingredients listed on hand, let's get started on our happy chore of putting together a good, wholesome, hearty marriage stew.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in bite-size pieces.
Mix in eggs, olives and onions.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together; shape into a ball.

title: hors d' oeuvre
directions: Shape into balls the sausage, grated cheese and Bisquick. Cook at 350° about 25 minutes.
Spread Old English sharp spread.

title: j. d.'s hush puppies
directions: Combine eggs, milk and onion and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in milk mixture until the dry ingredients are moist.
Drop by tablespoons into 375° oil.
Fry 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until tender (cool).
Remove chicken from bone.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Thicken broth with milk and flour.
Pepper to taste.
Boil until thick.
Pour thickened broth over chicken.
Cover chicken and place biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. In a medium bowl. mix butter, eggs, sugar, Karo syrup, vanilla and salt. Then stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Combine onion, leeks and garlic and cook, covered, over very low heat until soft, about 10 minutes, adding a little stock if necessary.
Add all the other ingredients except fish, shellfish and garnish.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add fish and shellfish and cook until it turns opaque, 2 to 5 minutes.
Serve garnished with fresh French bread.

title: pineapple-cool whip pie
directions: Empty pineapple and milk into bowl; mix well.
Add Cool Whip; mix thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and fold in real well.
Pour into cooled pie crust and put in refrigerator to chill and set.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk well, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well. Layer 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers (whole).
Put pudding mixture on, then repeat to the top.
Spread a can of chocolate frosting on top of crackers, then add nuts if desired.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar and walnuts well.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: steamed indian bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients in a good sized bowl.
Beat in the molasses and milk quickly for 2 minutes.
Grease a 1 pound coffee can and place wax paper around sides and bottom.
Fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Place foil over top and place in a covered kettle. Add water around the sides of the can.
Cover and steam for about 2 hours or until done.
Replenish water when necessary.
Serve sliced, hot and buttered.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: vegetable dip
directions: With mixer, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir in vegetables.
Better if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and margarine while potatoes are still warm.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Let cool and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cook potatoes at 350° until bubbly and the top of the potatoes have browned.
Serves a fairly large crowd (12 to 15).

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all and place in an 8-inch buttered casserole.
Top with toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: jiffy cracker jacks
directions: Heat honey and butter until blended.
Add to popcorn and stir. Spread mixture into two large pans.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
When cool, sit, and it's ready to eat.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, mix all the ingredients except the lemon slices and the shrimp.
Pour about a 1/2 cup sauce to cover the bottom of a large baking dish and then arrange layers of shrimp and lemon slices until you come almost to the top of the dish.
Leave about 1-inch of headroom.
Pour the remaining sauce over the shrimp and the lemon slices.
Bake, uncovered, stirring once or twice until the shrimp are cooked thoroughly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: uncooked boiled custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until thick.
Store in refrigerator.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla in dishpan.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto Pamed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 26 dozen.

title: cheeseburger onion pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Stir in onions, cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If onions begin to stick, add 2 tablespoons water.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Brown beef; drain fat.
Stir in ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper and set aside.
