Unroll 1 can of rolls and press together perforations.
Roll out to a 12-inch square.
Line a 9-inch pie pan.
Trim 1 inch beyond edge of dish.
Spoon meat into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with onions.
Pour 2 beaten eggs over top.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add tomato paste, water and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour 1 1/2 cups sauce in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with a layer of noodles and add more sauce.
Layer 1/2 of all the cheeses and the remaining noodles. Add the rest of the beef sauce and cheeses.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let set 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, fry bacon and drain.
Break up and add small bits to salad.
Serve.

title: turkey salad with pita bread
directions: Blend sour cream, green onions, dill weed and salt in medium bowl.
Add turkey and vegetables (except lettuce).
Toss to combine.
Serve on lettuce with pita bread or fill pita bread halves with turkey mixture and serve as sandwiches.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Melt 1 stick of margarine and add vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix well.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot crab dip supreme
directions: Stir cream cheese and butter together over medium heat until smooth.
Add crab meat, shrimp and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with crackers or bread cubes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Take a skillet, no grease no spray stuff.
Place chicken in the skillet as you would if you were going to fry it.
Do not use any oil, grease, or spray.
Turn the stove on medium and pour ketchup onto each piece of chicken, then salt and pepper it.
Pour the Coke over the chicken, covering it as you would if you were using cooking oil to fry it.
Let it cook until done.
You do not have to turn it, just check to see that it isn't sticking.
When it is done, it will be very tender and the Coke and ketchup will have made a BBQ sauce which is good.
Enjoy!

title: quick custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat first 4 ingredients until all sugar is dissolved.
Slowly add the scalded milk to the egg mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes or until custard is set.

title: dirty rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Spread rice in loaf pan. Add butter and soups.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour fruit, 1 cup sugar and water (in that order) over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimento; mix well. Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss butter with remaining crumbs. Sprinkle atop corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider with spices, sugar and lemon juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Strain and pour into punch bowl or crock-pot.
Float oranges in bowl.

title: curried fruit
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Arrange fruits in casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain the water from the tuna.
Give it to the cat.
Mix the tuna with 1 or 2 teaspoons of vinegar and 1 to 2 teaspoons olive oil. Add salt, pepper and Italian seasoning to taste.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and
onion
in skillet.
Put layers of beans and meat in casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over and cover with Tater Tots and bake in oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole. Bake for 40 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lite chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle cookie crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.

title: broccoli cheese strata
directions: Bring 1 1/2 quarts of water to a boil.
Add broccoli; bring back to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove broccoli from water; drain and place in bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine onion, pimiento, mayonnaise, lemon juice, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spoon half of mixture over broccoli.
Add cauliflower to water and cook 1 minute; drain and spoon in a layer over sauce in casserole dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over cauliflower and sprinkle evenly with bread crumbs and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare in long dish.
Cut into squares.

title: harvest rice
directions: In large skillet, cook carrots in oil about 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add onions and apples.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Serves 6.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: violet's swiss steak
directions: Sear steak in very hot skillet to seal the juices.
Brown onion with it, if wanted.
Put in roaster.
Add onions, green pepper, tomatoes, tomato sauce and celery.
Sprinkle garlic powder over all.
Add a sprinkle of Worcestershire sauce and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix well butter, Minute rice and cream of mushroom soup.
Add thawed broccoli and chunk up 5 or 6 slices of American cheese. Cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir well and let set a few minutes before serving.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine the pears, pecans and sugar; let set for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Mix all together.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (I cook mine at 325°).

title: beef patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into patties.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on each ham slice.
Place trimmed onion lengthwise at long end and carefully roll up. Repeat for each slice of ham.
They will look like little jelly rolls.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/2-inch slices.
Place "pinwheels" on serving platter or dish to serve.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese.
Add thawed strawberries.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Put out to thaw 1/2 hour before serving time.

title: unstuffed pepper soup(ready in one hour or less)
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, cool the beef, green peppers and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the broth, soup, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Bring o a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add rice; heat through.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: lima beans in sour cream
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover with fresh water and cook until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients adding sour cream last. One tablespoon molasses may be added.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated for several days.

title: banana bread
directions: Add the eggs to the sugar and mix with shortening and bananas. Sift the dry ingredients together and mix into the first mixture. Add nuts.
Put in a greased loaf pan.
Push batter up on sides of pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt the soup and cream cheese together in saucepan.
Mix gelatine and water, then add to the cream cheese mixture.
Add celery and onion.
Mix in shrimp.
Pour into "sprayed" mold. Serve with crackers.
Stand back to take a bow!

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in skillet; brown meat.
Stir in bay leaves, onions, celery, garlic, tomatoes, jalapeno and bell peppers. Saute for 10 minutes.
Add salt, peppers and black-eyed peas; simmer for 30 minutes.
Finally, add cooked rice; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
May be kept several days and reheated.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil in a large pan.
Turn off heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into well-greased and floured sheet pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Crumble cheese; add remaining ingredients with mixer or blender.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Drain sauerkraut and place in a saucepan.
Add mushrooms (undrained) and simmer 20 minutes. Fry the bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Drain.
In a large casserole, place meat, sauerkraut mixture and crumbled bacon.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add the last 2 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Bake for at least 2 hours at 375°.

title: rainbow magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs evenly.
Top with coconut, nuts, and M&M's and press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Yield:
24 to 36 bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: When fruit, marshmallows and pecans have been combined, pour over mixture cooled dressing.
Just before ready to serve, or a little sooner if desired, whip the whipping cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour over fruit and dressing mixture and mix well.

title: french dressing(diabetic)
directions: Combine vegetable oil, salt, dry mustard, paprika and hot sauce in a small bowl; stir and mix well.
Set aside.

title: grilled parmesan tomatoes
directions: Preheat broiler.
Grease a baking sheet with 1 teaspoon of the olive oil.
Arrange the tomato slices on it in a single layer.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta shells as directed.
Drain; toss with butter.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in cream cheese, taco seasoning and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Fill shells with meat mixture.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon taco sauce over shells.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheese and chips and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Put cake mix into large mixing bowl.
Add the Jell-O, egg yolks, apricot nectar, oil and lemon extract.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites separately and fold into the batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
While cake bakes, prepare glaze.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in a 9-inch square pan.
Combine cake mix and butter mixture.
Will be crumbly. Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: birthday bananas
directions: Use all you want of good vanilla ice cream.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix together next 4 ingredients until well blended.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread bag of mini marshmallows over the top.
Return to the oven until marshmallows are slightly brown (5 to 10 minutes).
Cool completely.
Spread with frosting.

title: squash supreme
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Pour in half of stuffing.
Mix the squash, onion, soup, sour cream, carrot and pepper; spoon mixture over top of stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces.
Brown ground meat until done; drain and rinse.
Add seasoning, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add corn chips.
Pour dressing over mixture; toss well.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cut up chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and salt and pepper (if desired).
Add 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spoon this mixture over chicken until covered. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 300°
for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach-mushroom quiche(serves 6)
directions: Beat eggs with cream in medium mixing bowl.
Stir in pepper, salt, nutmeg and Swiss cheese.

title: lemon-flavored pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix at high speed 6 to 8 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: recipe for a christian cook
directions: Hands on hips.
Place 1 cup of flour on shoulder.
Raise knees and depress toes and mix thoroughly. 1 cup milk.
Repeat 6 times. Inhale quickly 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Lower legs and mash 2 hard-boiled eggs in a sieve.
Exhale.
Breath naturally, and sift into a bowl.
Attention!
Lie flat on the floor and roll the white of an egg backward and forward until it comes to a boil.
In 10 minutes, remove from fire and rub smartly with a rough towel. Breath naturally, dress in warm flannel and serve with soup.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix both together and add carrots and nuts. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, the flour and salt; add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Mix small amount of mixture with beaten egg yolks and return to double boiler.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
In large serving dish, put a layer of the cookies, layer of mixture, banana layer and sprinkle with little lemon juice. Repeat until all is used, then top with meringue.
Beat egg whites until stands in peaks; add the 4 to 6 tablespoons sugar and about 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Spread on top of the pudding.
Bake until just tan color.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar and add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Make golf ball sized cookies. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in rest of ingredients; spread over tortillas.
Roll up tight and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Slice and serve with picante sauce on the side.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Use tube pan and grease with a small portion of shortening. Sprinkle flour over the shortening. Cook 2 hours in heated oven.
Don't open oven.
Take out and cover it with a towel before turning out.

title: even better the next day casserole
directions: Fry bacon until it starts to get crisp.
Then add onion and green pepper and continue frying for a few minutes.
Then add ground beef and cook until tender and browned.
When well done, add tomatoes, cooked spaghetti and mushrooms and simmer on a low heat for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then pour into 2 medium-size greased casseroles.
Sprinkle with sharp cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good the first day, but "even better the next" as the flavors blend.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine to soft ball stage (236°), stirring often.
Remove from heat, add chocolate chips, marshmallows, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted. Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score, cool and cut in squares.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and sweeten with milk. Layer with bananas and crackers. Repeat layers and crumble crackers on top.

title: calzones
directions: Mix all cheeses, parsley and ham, if desired, together. Separate defrosted bread dough into 8 pieces and roll out into a circle about 8 inches across.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 cup of cheese mixture on one side of dough circle.
Fold other half over to make a semi-circle.
Pinch edges to seal.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until dough is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add soups to rice and place in baking dish.
Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine.
Place meat on top of rice mixture and bake, covered, 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 350°.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil in a Dutch oven.
Remove meat and set aside.
Saute onions and garlic in drippings until tender.
Return roast to Dutch oven and add cut up tomatoes and remaining ingredients using 1/2 water.
Cover and cook until meat is tender about 2 or 3 hours.
Remove roast to serving platter, keeping it warm.
Add flour and remaining water to pan juices.
Cook for about 5 minutes until thick and bubbly.
Slice roast and serve with gravy.

title: molded cranberry-red raspberry salad
directions: Chop or grind cranberries and orange in blender.
Mix in sugar and nuts.
In saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water to boil.
Stir in gelatin, remove from heat and continue stirring until dissolved. Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups water and then add to cranberry mixture; mix well.
Rinse a 6-cup mold and fill with mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Decorate with celery leaves.
Serve over lettuce.

title: rice plus
directions: Wash and cook rice.
Add sugar and butter.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover top with marshmallows and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in oven until marshmallows are brown and puffed.

title: oreo delight
directions: Prepare 2 boxes pudding as directed.
Put in refrigerator to chill and thicken.
Crumble 2/3 of Oreos over bottom of long casserole dish.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese, then mix pudding with Cool Whip/cream cheese mixture.
Pour over Oreos.
Crumble remaining 1/3 Oreos over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°
Grease a 9
inch pie plate.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with hand mixer. Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato and zucchini slices if desired.
Makes 6 servings

title: mandarin pork roast
directions: Spread marmalade over pork roast.
Place roast on rack in shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb is centered in thickest part.
Do not add water; do not cover.
Roast at 325°
in oven until thermometer reads 155° to 160°, about 1 hour.
Let roast rest 10 minutes before carving.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Chop onion.

Alternate layers with potatoes, onion, garlic salt and butter in large casserole dish. Mix Cheddar cheese soup with milk and pour over potatoes. (Additional milk can be added if needed.) Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: cherry delight dump cake
directions: Dump cherry filling into bottom of casserole.
Dump the pineapple, then sprinkle cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
On top of this, add Angel Flake coconut and top with the pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: poppy form cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add poppy seed filling, then egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and add gradually to poppy seed mixture, beating well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pan which has bottom lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Confectioners sugar can be sifted on cake.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put 3 cans of red beans in crock-pot (save the fourth can to be used later). Cut sausage crosswise into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces and add.
Turn crock-pot to high and let beans and sauce begin to cook.
Add chopped vegetables and spices.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
The amount needed will depend on spices in sausage and on your individual taste.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Turn crock-pot to low and let mixture cook for 8 hours.

title: baked onions and stewed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tomatoes and spices in baking dish.
Stir to mix.
Place onions in dish and spoon tomato mixture over.
Cover dish and place in preheated oven to bake for 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Salt and pepper potatoes.
Pare and dice potatoes.
Cook potatoes and onion in boiling water until tender.
Scald milk. Add oleo and milk to potatoes and reheat.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash potatoes as usual.
When lumps are removed, add cream cheese and butter.
Beat until well blended.
Add sour cream.
Pour beaten eggs into milk; add to mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Be sure mixture is thin.

title: bing candy
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cherry chips and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Heat peanut butter, chocolate chips and peanuts.
Spread on top of cherry mixture.

title: classic turkey divan
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in nutmeg. Gently fold in whipped whipping cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Place cooked broccoli in ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with turkey slices.
Pour sauce over meat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Set oven control at broil or 550°.
Broil 3 to 5-inches from heat or until cheese is golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce (canned)
directions: Extract juice from tomatoes.
Cook with tomatoes for 1 1/2 hours.
Then add oil, sugar, salt, oregano, basil and tomato paste.
Cook for 45 minutes and seal.
Cold pack 50 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie(low-fat, low-sodium)
directions: Heat oil; add onion.
Stir often until tender.
Combine flour, bouillon, thyme and pepper.
Stir into onion mixture.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Fill pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly and brown.
Serves 8.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, shortening, eggs, baking powder, salt and extracts.
Beat, scraping bowl occasionally, until well blended.
Stir in flour, mixing well. Spoon 2/3 of batter into 9-inch greased square pan.
Evenly spread pie filling over batter.
Using tablespoon, drop remaining batter over the top (pie filling will not be completely covered).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: doris' cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, oil, water and vinegar in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Chop cabbage, bell pepper and onion and toss with celery seed.
Add cooled dressing. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and egg; beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in chopped apple. Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil, about 370° and at least 2 1/2 to 3-inches deep.
Fry for about 2 to 3 minutes until nicely browned.
Drain well on paper towels, then roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Serve as is or warm with syrup, if desired.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beginning with potato chips, layer chips, shredded tuna and mushroom soup in as many layers as needed to fill casserole, ending with potato chips.
Bake uncovered until heated through and chips are lightly browned (about 30 minutes).

title: applesauce cake
directions: *Put soda in applesauce and let turn dark.

title: four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Follow graham cracker crust recipe.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass pan; press firmly.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add gelatin mixture to boiling tomato juice.
Add ketchup, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into molds.
Chill.
Can serve with shrimp salad.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix in remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain; add seasoning mix, water and olives. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: calico bean salad
directions: In a saucepan cook the frozen lima beans and black-eyed peas in 1 cup water according to package directions, except add the chicken bouillon granules and basil.
Drain; set aside to cool. When cool combine lima beans, black-eyed peas, kidney beans, garbanzo beans, sweet red pepper, celery, green onions and parsley; toss.

title: cottage potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine potatoes and next 5 ingredients.
Spoon into a 9-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
About 90 calories per serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: *You may use 1 can of cream of celery soup and 1/2 cup of celery instead of mushroom soup and mushrooms.

title: creamy chicken fettuccine toss
directions: Prepare fettuccine as package directs.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine; stir in flour, broth, basil, garlic powder and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk; cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
In large serving bowl, combine hot cooked fettuccine and sauce; toss to coat.
Serve immediately with cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scallops and asparagus in mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add scallops and cook 10 minutes; drain.
Place scallops and mushrooms in buttered baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Blend until smooth.
Add asparagus and cover with mixture.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash, onion, salt and pepper in bacon drippings.
Mix all the other ingredients with the squash; put into casserole dish and spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sunshine salad dessert
directions: Open all cans and drain, reserving the juice.
Make pudding according to directions, except use the drained juices instead of the milk called for.
Let this mixture cool.
Allow fruit to continue draining while glaze is cooling.

title: maymie's drop cookies
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add the chocolate chips. Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop dough with teaspoon.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned plain custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until bubbly.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add 3 tablespoons to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add this to remainder of milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 450° oven.
After 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Allow pie to cool before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: banana cream pie or coconut pie
directions: Melt butter, blend in corn starch, sugar and salt. Gradually add milk. Heat to boiling over direct heat. Stir constantly to keep it from sticking or burning. Pour into eggs stirring rapidly. Pour back into the pan. Continue cooking for two minutes, adding 1 c. coconut and vanilla (if you want coconut pie, Omit coconut if you want banana cream). When pudding has cooled, layer in pie shell with bananas and pudding for banana cream. If you have made coconut, cool down and pour into baked pie shell.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish; bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pilaf(serves 4)
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan over low heat.
Add rice and stir-fry about 5 minutes, until straw-colored.
Add broth, salt and pepper. Cover and cook over low heat until all liquid is absorbed.
Uncover and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer to dry out.
Fluff with a fork. Contains 305 calories per serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. While cake bakes, make the Buttermilk Sauce to pour over when it comes from the oven.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend sugar and canola oil. Add eggs and pumpkin. Blend. Add nuts and raisins.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Bake in ungreased bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: texas barbecue
directions: True Texas barbecue starts with a large brisket which is smoked over hickory or mesquite wood for 24 hours at low temperature.
Personally, I don't like to sit up all night babysitting a fire, so I simplified the method.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time and frozen, then baked for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to boil; add peanut butter and cook until smooth, stirring frequently.
Add to cereal in very large bowl.
Stir quickly but thoroughly and pour into greased pans. Cool and cut.
Makes 1 (13 x 9-inch) and 1 (8 x 8-inch) pan.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Finely chop some pecans and mash into unbaked pie crusts. Bake pie crusts and cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions.
Mix Dream Whip with cream cheese mixture.
Pour into cool pie crusts; top with pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine with cracker crumbs.
Beat remaining margarine with powdered sugar and eggs for 15 minutes.
Pat crumbs in an 8 x 8-inch cake pan or pie tin.
Spread egg mixture over crumbs.
Slice bananas and sprinkle pineapple on top.
Add whipped topping and dot with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: molten chocolate cakes(make ahead prep time:  19 minutes cook time:  11 minutes.)
directions: Brush 15 muffin cups with 2 Tbsp. melted butter. Sprinkle evenly with cocoa shaking out excess.
Place in refrigerator to firm butter.

title: fried venison with mushroom sauce
directions: Cut venison into small cubes.
Salt.
Roll in flour and fry in skillet of hot oil.
Cook until tender and brown.
Drain off oil from skillet.
Add the mushroom soup to the venison.
This makes a delicious sauce.

title: baked squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash and onion with seasonings. Mash thoroughly; drain excess water.
Add cracker crumbs and egg to squash mixture.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; continue baking until cheese has melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pistachio cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray bottom of dish with Pam.
Line pan with buttered bread. Cook sausage; drain and pour over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over sausage and cheese.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake next day for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce, ground chuck and water in a bowl. cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Layer 4 noodles, 1/2 the Ricotta, 1/2 the Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another layer of sauce mixture.
Repeat with noodles, cheese and sauce.
Top with noodles.
Pour remaining sauce over, spreading evenly to cover edges of noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Set on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife goes easily through pasta.
Let stand, covered, on rack for 10 minutes.

title: brunch recipe
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour on top of bread mixture.
(Can be mixed the night before and kept refrigerated.)

title: apricot envelopes
directions: Combine flour, salt, butter, lemon peel and cream cheese to make dough.
Roll dough on floured board.
Cut into squares.
Fill center with preserves.
Fold ends over, brush with beaten egg white and put nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Into a large bowl, measure all the ingredients.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl. Shape dough into ball; wrap with waxed paper.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours until easy to handle.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Add chips. Spoon on ungreased sheet; mash with a fork. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Makes 1 serving, 3 proteins, 1 vegetable and 1 bread.

title: tofu and corn quiche
directions: Spread margarine over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs to coat the dish.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: layered taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of shallow casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Spread guacamole over beans.

Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix. Spread mixture over guacamole. Top with tomatoes, green chilies and green onions. Top with mixed cheeses. Top with black olives. Serve layered mixture with nacho chips.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Fold into whipped cream.
Chill.

title: beef goulash
directions: Heat oil in deep saucepan.
Add beef cubes and onions. Sprinkle with flour and cook until lightly browned.
Stir in paprika and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomato puree, water, salt, sugar, pepper, bay leaf and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: summertime chili
directions: Tips:
To prepare in advance, the chili can be made in advanced through Step 3 and refrigerated overnight.
Skim off congealed fat. Continue with rest of recipe.
No extra salt is needed as the broth and tomatoes contain salt.
The vinegar adds a tang.
Prepare: Brown beef in 1 tablespoon hot oil.
Stir occasionally but leave large crumbles of meat.
Add onions, garlic, peppers and celery, cooking until softened.
Skim the fat; stir in spices and cook 1 or 2 minutes.
Add broth, vinegar and tomatoes.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer covered for 45 minutes.
Add olives; break the corn ears into halves or thirds. slice zucchini in half lengthwise and then crosswise in large chunks.
Place corn and zucchini on top of chili.
Cover and cook slowly 20 or 30 minutes.
Serve in bowls. Top with corn and zucchini and cornbread.

title: simmered red wings
directions: Discard tip on wings, disjoint others.
Combine other ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Add wings.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 15 minutes

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
(You may want to use less water.
I use more coconut and it worked.
Otherwise it has a tendency to run when you invert it.)

title: zebra cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and oil together.
Add one egg at a time. Then add rest of ingredients.
Let chill overnight.
Take teaspoon of dough and roll in ball.
Roll in powdered sugar and white sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Soon as they come out of oven, place a Hershey's Hug in center. Let cool 1 hour.

title: 3 week slaw
directions: Shred regular and red cabbage.
Shred onions.
Add sugar and mix well.
Heat and boil remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Will keep 3 weeks.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar with Wesson oil.
Add eggs.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 hour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Have syrup ready and pour over hot cake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix flour and cheese. Add soft butter and season to taste. Run through cookie press. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix,
egg
and softened butter.
Press into ungreased 9 x
13-inch
pan.
Mix
confectioners
sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs.	Pour this over first batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix and make into ball; put 1/2 can of tomato sauce in bottom of pot.
Put cabbage rolls in; put other half of tomato on top.

title: mama's throw together
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onion.
Add pepperoni, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Return to pan and add pizza sauce.
Cook all macaroni together until tender.
Drain.
Mix meat, sauce and noodles together.
Put into baking pan and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven about 25 minutes, basically until cheese is melted.

title: cherries a la mode
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sharon prose's peanut butter candy
directions: Melt the sugar, butter and evaporated milk; let it come to a boil for about 4 minutes or 5.
Remove from burner, then add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: chicken and three peppers salad
directions: In a medium bowl, gently stir together chunk chicken and peppers.
In a cup, stir together olive oil, vinegar, basil, oregano and garlic.
Pour dressing over chicken and peppers.
Toss gently and serve on salad greens.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs.
Form into crust in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In skillet, cook meat, onions and green pepper until tender and brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano, salt and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Fill pie with tomato mixture. Cover with foil and chill 2 to 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 5 minutes more.

title: nacho pie
directions: Heat chili in medium saucepan over medium heat. Empty soup and milk in a small saucepan and heat thoroughly; stirring until smooth and creamy. Crush tortilla chips into bottom of individual serving bowls. When chili and soup are hot, scoop chili over chips. Pour soup over chili. Sprinkle with chopped onions and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples, 1/4 cup orange juice and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat margarine at medium speed until creamy. Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Beat until creamy (5 minutes).
Add egg substitute.
Beat 4 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup orange juice and milk.
Add in flour, baking powder and salt to margarine mixture with milk mixture.
Begin and end with flour.
Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Top with apple mixture.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Calories:

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in cheese, bread and sausage.
Pour in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine drained kidney beans, green pepper, celery, onion, salt and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion over the bottom of the pie shell.
Beat eggs and half and half and spices.
Pour into a pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: creamy strawberry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together until smooth, the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, lemon rind and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pearl's salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 2 cups boiling water and add 1 cup cold water; chill until syrupy.
Add celery, pineapple, cheese and then Dream Whip.
Chill.
When serving, you can put a small amount of mayonnaise on each serving and put a cherry on it.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: shoepeg casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese; add flour, milk, salt and jalapenos.
Heat oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put in a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed.
Press on pizza pan.
Bake as directed and cool. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread on cookie dough. Add fruit and arrange to your liking.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown beef and onions until done.
Season to taste, then add beans and simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Add a little water, if needed.
Great over cooked rice.

title: football stew
directions: Put stew meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer onion, carrots, potatoes and celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with sugar and cornstarch.
Pour V-8 juice on top.
Cover and bake 3 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: crab critter fritters
directions: Remove all cartilage from crab meat.
In a bowl, beat egg; add milk and stir in biscuit mix.
Add seasonings and crab meat and gently mix.

title: ruth richardson's cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses set at room temperature until soft.
Add other ingredients and blend with a fork.
Chill overnight.
Roll into a ball and then roll in a mixture of 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.

title: pork apple kraut
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from pork chops or ribs, but leave bones in.
If 1/2-inch thick, cut chops in half or ribs can be cut into chunks.
Brown meat in skillet on all sides.
Remove to a casserole.
Add dash of pepper on each piece.
Drain sauerkraut in colander and rinse quickly with cold water.
Place in the skillet and stir around to absorb the meat residue for flavor.
Wash and core apples but leave skin on.
Cut into rings approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Layer the pork and sauerkraut in a casserole and top with the apple rings.
Sprinkle each apple with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: corned beef and cabbage(this recipe is good any time, not just on st. patrick's day.)
directions: Place the corned beef brisket in a large pan and cover with water.
Boil for 3 hours or until tender when jabbed with a fork. (Keep adding water to keep pan from boiling dry.)
Save brine (or broth) and place in a large kettle.
In brine, cook cabbage, potatoes, carrots and onions until tender.
Slice beef and serve with vegetables.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine onion, butter, cheese and soup into saucepan.
Heat until mixture is melted.
Pour into casserole dish over hominy. Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sprinkle fruit dip
directions: In a bowl, fold together yogurt, whipped topping and half of the sprinkles. Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes. Just before serving, top with remaining sprinkles. Serve with fruit.

title: pudding poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Immediately poke holes down through cake to pan with round handle or straw, using a turning motion.

title: peter's pumpkin delight dessert
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat well.
Pour into large buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle white cake mix over top.
Be sure mix has no lumps.
Press cake mix into mixture, using knife in a chopping motion, blade cutting into mixture.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted margarine over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: brown sugar sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add sugar, stirring always.
Add boiling water.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flavoring.

title: aunt kate's no-bake cookies
directions: Put first four ingredients into a large saucepan.
After it starts to boil, cook for two minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oats, marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and refrigerate until hardened.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine other ingredients in jar; shake.
Pour over vegetables; toss gently. Cover and chill 24 hours.

title: spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: funsten pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, corn syrup and butter. Stir in pecans. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain and cut into smaller pieces.
Add Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add pieces of tomatoes and other veggies.
Toss together and chill.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Drain vertical pack long green beans. Wrap 6 beans in 1/2 slice of bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Marinate in melted butter and brown sugar overnight.

title: super veggie casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Pour mixture into 9x13 casserole dish.
Melt margarine, add Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lean chili
directions: Coat a heavy stew pot with no stick spray, i.e. Pam.
Brown ground meat and onion, stirring often.
If desired, drain off fat. Add next ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
To thicken, combine corn meal and 1/4 cup of water; add to chili and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and discard juice.
Drain strawberries and pineapple.
Mix juice with large package instant pudding and 3 tablespoons Tang.
Pour juice mixture over fruit and chill.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add beaten eggs and cook without stirring until set.
Invert skillet over a baking sheet to remove cooked edges.
Cut into short, narrow strips.

title: cow pie chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and add seasonings and tomatoes.
Add melted cheese.
Put in crock-pot.
Serve warm over nachos or other chips of your choice.

title: mango black bean salad
directions: Toss main ingredients and fruit in large bowl.
Mix salad dressing with salsa.
Combine fruit mixture and salsa, dressing mixture.
Yield 6 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except parsley flakes and pimento.
Add these 2 ingredients last.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Form into 2 cheese balls and roll in nuts, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze. Thaw about 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix cheese and baking mix.
Shape into a roll about 1-inch diameter.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; turn roll as you cut to keep them round.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: amy's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water until al dente. Drain and rinse in cold water.
In a small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, cider vinegar, mustard, sugar, black pepper, dill weed and salt.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, grapes, ham, green onions and cheese.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and chill overnight or for at least 6 hours.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Roll in bread crumbs or corn flakes.
Fry in hot deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fish florentine
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, flour and garlic.
Stir until thickened.
Spray bottom and sides of baking dish with Pam. Spoon layer of sauce in bottom of pan.
Place spinach on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Arrange fish on top of spinach. Sprinkle with black pepper.
Pour remainder of sauce over fish. Sprinkle with cheese and dust with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 30 minutes or until fish is flaky.
Serve with wild rice.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon color.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Baking time may vary according to size of pan.
Test with toothpick.

title: sandwich cheese bake
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 4 sandwiches using some of the mustard and 2 slices of cheese for each.
Place side by side in prepared pan.
With a fork, beat eggs, milk and salt in a bowl until well blended.
Pour over sandwiches.
Cut remaining 2 slices of cheese in half.
Place 1 piece of cheese on each sandwich.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or up to 24.
Cook at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes; remove and let stand 10 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: the alice's brunswick stew
directions: Boil hen until it falls to pieces.
Remove bones and skin. Chop chicken in small pieces.
Add all vegetables (except potatoes) and cook in broth with chicken until it can be eaten with a fork.
Cook potatoes separately, mash and add to stew to thicken.
Stew scorches easily and should be stirred frequently as it begins to thicken.

title: crab dip
directions: Just slightly warm the mushroom soup in pan.
Add the gelatine which has been softened in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise and blend well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin cookie bites
directions: Mix all together and chill until dough is firm.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll out 10 x 14-inch in plastic wrap.
Freeze 4 hours. May be frozen up to 4 months.

title: cranberry velvet
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, pineapple, lemon juice and salt. Mix well. Prepare whipped topping (with water). Use only half bag. Fold marshmallows and whipped topping into cranberry mixture. Chill until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Boil rice and drain; mix with chopped broccoli.
Microwave Cheez Whiz.
Mix with soup.
Combine all ingredients together. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling and golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no fat dill dip
directions: Mix and chill 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature and knead together.
Add garlic and chili powders and blend well.
Add pecans and knead once more.
Divide into 2 balls and roll into logs.
Sprinkle chili powder onto foil and roll up in foil.
Close tightly.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together with fork; spread over the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 18 regular muffin cups.
Beat butter and sugar in a medium size bowl until pale yellow and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Spoon into an unbaked pie crust.
Top with the remaining crust; crimp edges to seal.
Cut slits in top crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Blend well and add oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 370° for 1 hour.

title: best ever salad
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a blender with the hot water. Blend until mixed.
Let stand until begins to jell.
Add the pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: purple cow
directions: Place 3 scoops of ice cream into a tall glass.
Pour 8 ounces of juice into glass.
Stir a little.
Add a spoon and a straw.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; after they cook, cool and peel off skin.
Chop potatoes.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Chop eggs.
Add all ingredients together.
Depending on the size of the potatoes, more mayonnaise may need to be added or subtracted.
Refrigerate for several hours.
This will feed about 12 people.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk. Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Just before serving, add the crushed cookies.

title: swiss steak pot pie
directions: Break up Swiss steaks in 1-inch pieces.
Saute onion slightly. Mix all ingredients together and put into pie shell.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie shell is done.

title: varenyky-ukranian potato dumplings
directions: Mix together and knead lightly.
Set aside in bowl covered with a kitchen towel.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy with low speed of mixer.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder; add small amount of flour mixture at a time to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
When all flour has been added, remove mixture and fold in chopped apples.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan; line bottom with wax paper and spray with Pam.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix, water, eggs and oil and beat according to box directions. Pour batter over coconut/pecans.
In saucepan, combine cream cheese and butter.
Melt over low heat.
May use mixer to thoroughly combine.
Add powdered sugar.
Pour over batter, being careful not to pour too close to the sides of the pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cool 10 minutes and invert into a serving platter.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix, margarine and 2 beaten eggs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs (beaten until frothy).
Pour over cake mixture already in pan.
Top with pecans. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first five ingredients.
Sift salt, soda and flour together and add.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop a teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Remove skin from chicken; boil chicken until tender and debone.
In a large pot, combine chicken and remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: caramel nut bars
directions: Mix all together and spread in greased and floured pan.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 1 cup light brown sugar and 1 cup nuts. Pour over batter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda, then add oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over mixture. Mix until smooth (don't heat).
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels and sugar.
Add margarine, stirring until well combined.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 6 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and then add all other ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain.
Add sour cream, taco seasoning and diced Ro-Tel to meat mixture.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

Stuff meat mixture into prepared pasta and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, reserving 1 cup of meat mixture to pour over stuffed pasta. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake in a 350° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken pasta casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, green pepper in oleo.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and olives.
Add meat or chicken, if desired. Simmer uncovered for a few minutes.
Place half of the spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.

title: apple cake
directions: Sprinkle apples with sugar mixed with cinnamon and raisins.

title: chocolate candy bar dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly into bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 10 minutes. Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup of sugar in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 of whipped topping.
Spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle chopped candy bars over cream cheese layer.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire wisk 1 minute.
Pour over candy bars.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with additional candy bars.
Cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
In heavy skillet, heat margarine and add garlic.
Cook, stirring briefly, without browning.
Add shrimp and stir briefly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until shrimp are no longer translucent (about 5 minutes).
Do not overcook. Serve over rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, 1/3 cup of water and 1/2 cup pineapple chunks, cut up.
Shape into small balls.
Bring sauce to boil; add meatballs and remaining pineapple chunks.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes or until done.
Serve hot in chafing dish. Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone or just add chopped dates.
Add applesauce, eggs, liquid, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Mix together the dry ingredients and blend in with the applesauce mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a loaf pan or tube pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add peach slices and coat well.
Cook peach mixture in a saucepan over medium heat until peaches are tender and mixture is thickened.
Stir frequently; set aside.
Mix together Bisquick, milk, 2 tablespoons of sugar and melted butter until stiff.
Can add 1 more tablespoon of milk if mixture is too stiff.
Pour peach mixture into greased casserole.
Pour Bisquick mixture on top in dollops.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of sugar over top of cobbler.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oven stew (beef or venison)
directions: Cook all ingredients (except potatoes, carrots and onion) for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion.
Bake for another 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together with squash.
Grease a baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake casserole at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until browned on top.

title: herbed chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, sage and thyme,
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In large skillet over medium high heat, in hot butter, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, combine soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in hot cooking oil.
Add onions, tomatoes, chilies, garlic and beef stock; bring to a boil.
Simmer until rice is soft and all moisture is removed.

title: creamy chicken chowder
directions: Mix ingredients together in a crock-pot or saucepan and heat on low or medium heat until warm.
Do not boil.
This can be made ahead, covered and refrigerated for up to 3 days.
When reheating, do not let the soup boil or it will curdle.

title: terry's fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit in bowl.
Sprinkle vanilla pudding mix over fruit.
Mix Tang with pineapple juice and pour over fruit and pudding mixture.
Chill overnight and decorate with kiwi slices.

title: creamed turkey
directions: Saute in skillet butter, onion and celery until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add 4 cups milk; cook until it is thick.
Add 4 cups diced turkey.
Serve over toast or toasted buns.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, nuts and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish. Refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Carefully add remaining Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: quick bake fish fillets
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add Worcestershire sauce and milk. Dip fish into milk mixture, then wheat flakes.
Place in greased shallow baking pan.
Drip on melted butter.
Bake in a hot oven of 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until easily flaked and moist.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 4 to 5 tablespoons butter.
Cook rice for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix onion and rice together and add Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and milk.
Add cooked broccoli (cook broccoli for 5 minutes).
Stir until blended.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top each corner with dabs of butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucy sausages
directions: Mix all ingredients well in crock-pot or saucepan.
Heat well and serve with toothpicks.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine 1 1/2 minutes at a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until smooth.
Add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool until hardened.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Do not brown meat first.
Cut potatoes, carrots, celery and onions into chunky size pieces and layer on top of meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix tomato sauce with water, sugar and tapioca and pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Seal tightly with aluminum foil and place in 325° oven for 3 hours. When foil is removed, meat will be nicely browned with gravy.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Cut into squares and roll in granulated sugar.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken well done.
Take chicken out of broth.
Cool. Tear chicken into strips.
Mix cream, eggs and flour together. Knead well.
Place on wax paper.
Sprinkle dough with flour.
Roll dough with dough roller.
Cut into small squares.
Have broth simmering.
Drop about 8 or 9 drops of food coloring into broth. Place dough squares into broth.
After dumplings are done, stir in chicken strips.

title: jimmy cake
directions: Mix in order given, except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in blender while still frozen.
Combine with next 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Top with marshmallows.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill until set.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. In blender, mix the remaining ingredients. Combine and drop by tablespoonful in hot grease.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and sherry.
In greased baking dish layer ham slices, chicken breasts and cheese slices.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: quick bake pasta
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic; saute until the meat is tender and then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheese for topping and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks and just barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix with the sauce.
Pour all into a 3-quart baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and set aside.
Pour boiling water over chocolate.
Place over hot water (double boiler works best) and stir until well blended.
Remove chocolate mixture from hot water and add gelatin.
Beat egg yolks.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar, a little at a time.
Fold egg yolks, whites and chocolate mixture together.
Fold in angel food cake and pour in spring-form pan; refrigerate overnight.
Makes eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Form the mixture into a ball and refrigerate before serving.

title: ambrosia platter
directions: Arrange the fruit in a visually appealing pattern on a lettuce lined platter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Chill.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix and press in a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: herbed beef stew
directions: Heat oil.
Cover stew beef with flour and add to oil.
Brown over medium-high heat.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, wine, garlic, salt, herbs, pepper and bay leaves.
Once boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Add vegetables and cook one hour longer.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to egg mixture with cocoa and oil.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken salad appetizer
directions: Roll out slices of bread with crusts cut off.
Cut into 1/4's. Press in miniature cupcake pans.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
Fill each crust with chicken salad.
Top with pickles, chips or olives.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In
bowl
with	mixer
at medium speed, beat margarine, peanut butter,
sugar,
brown
sugar,
eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Add
flour,
baking soda, baking powder and salt; mix well with large
spoon.
Shape
into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place
2-inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 15-inch pan, place deboned chicken; mix soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and melted butter and pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for thirty minutes, then turn oven up to 400° long enough to brown.
Serves 6.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in remaining 3 cups flour to make batter stiff.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into 8-inch square glass pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle over apples and cake mixture.
Toss lightly.
Drizzle margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Add Wesson oil, pumpkin, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill evenly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be served as slices or spread slices with cream cheese and cut in quarters.
Will keep well in freezer.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender; blend for 10 seconds (4 times).
Pour into 10-inch buttered and floured pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie will be done when top is golden brown.
It makes its own crust and looks like custard pie.

title: ginny's best baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion and bell pepper in bacon fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 2 hours at 350° or cook in crock-pot all day on low.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add slightly beaten eggs to the cream mixture; beat completely.
Add sifted flour mixture to cream mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla. Stir in 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: cocktail quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let oleo, cream cheese and eggs come to room temperature.
Combine oleo, cream cheese and flour and press into miniature muffin tins.
Layer in muffin tins:
chives, Parmesan cheese, ham and Swiss cheese in that order.
Mix eggs, half and half, salt and pepper and garlic.
Pour this mixture over the layered ingredients.
(Do this very slowly and make sure each muffin is filled.)
Bake for 20 minutes.
If freezing, bake for 15 minutes and freeze.
Remove from freezer; bake for 15 minutes and freeze.
Remove from freezer; let defrost.
Bake for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla; fluff again.
In separate bowl, add boiling water to sugar and gelatine; whip with whisk.
Add sugar mixture to cheese; slowly beat until smooth.
Pour into crust; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Add cherries to top.

title: party crunchie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking pan.
In buttered pan, stir in cheese and seasoning.
Add cereal, pretzel and peanuts, stirring until well coated.
Bake 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage in frying pan.
When done, drain grease from pan. Scramble eggs and add 1/2 cup of milk to scrambled eggs; mix well.
Add scrambled eggs to cooked sausage and cook until eggs are done.
Microwave hash browns for approximately 7 minutes or until you feel they are done.
Add hash browns to cooked sausage and eggs for 5 minutes.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into eggs and then into bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a medium skillet, heat oil. Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned on both sides.

title: jessie's special p.b. sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on each slice of bread.
Arrange apples, carrots, Cheez-Its and raisins to make funny faces.

title: tuna mac and cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions in large saucepan. Drain. Return to pan. Stir in cheese, milk and herb. Heat and stir until cheese is melted. Add peas and carrots and tuna. Heat through.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Mix together and put in greased baking dish.
Top with 4 ounces of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunflower seed bars
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all dry ingredients together.
Add peanut butter, honey and oil and mix well.
Spread into pan and pat down well.
Bake for 25 minutes. Let cool for 1 hour before cutting into bars.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and sherry.
Place chicken in casserole; pour mixture over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or at 275° for 3 hours, depending upon your time and where you want to go while it is cooking.
Serve on rice with the gravy.

title: grandma's waffles
directions: Place dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat until smooth, 2 minutes.
Bake in hot, greased waffle iron.
Yields 12 waffles.

title: english pepper-pot
directions: Grease pan.
Put in hamburger, tomatoes, vegetables and salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 375° about 2 1/2 hours .
Cover with lid to bake.

title: creme cheese-pumpkin roll recipe
directions: Beat eggs gradually; add sugar.
Blend in the pumpkin, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and flour.
Spread onto a greased waxed papered cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts over dough.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn out onto a towel covered with some powdered sugar.
Roll the towel into a log.
Let cool.

title: mom beard's never fail noodles
directions: Mix together in order given.
Add flour.
Roll out and cut. May be used fresh or let dry.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Boil large pan of salted water.
Add tortellini and cook about 10 minutes and add rotini to same pan and continue cooking.
Drain pasta and run under cold water to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and pour salad dressing over it and toss well.
Stir occasionally to marinate well.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake in a 375° oven until sharp knife comes out clean when inserted near the center, about 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook
and
drain
macaroni.
Beat eggs and add to milk; add pepper.
Pour
into greased casserole dish over macaroni. Add diced cheese and margarine on top.	Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: The night before serving cut up, fry and drain bacon.
Cut up green onions and mix with mayonnaise and pepper and refrigerate. Break up cauliflower buds and mix with the mixture.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot, pepper and salt. Let stand 1 hour.
Place in sauce pan the vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Cool.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 minutes or until solid.

title: brown bread
directions: Dissolve soda in molasses and hot water, then add to other ingredients.

title: bologna sandwich breakfast
directions: Put bologna slices between bread slices.

title: mexican skillet
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until rice is done.
Makes 6 cups.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken with bouillon cubes until done (in enough water to make enough broth to cook vegetables).
Remove chicken from broth; cool.
Add vegetables and cook according to package directions.
When done, add cream of chicken soup; stir to well blend soup and vegetables.
Broth is smooth.
Add canned milk.
If too thin, thicken with flour and water to desired consistency. Add chicken pieces; pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Top with biscuits or pie crust.
Bake until topping is done, according to package directions.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic and onion.
Cook until tender over moderate heat.
Stir in the flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add clam juice and stir until thickened.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Coat crackers with seasoning.
Drain on paper towels.
Store in airtight containers.

title: rice francis
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add salt.
Let set 1 hour and drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and water; boil this for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Add shredded carrot and green pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Cool and freeze.

title: string beans supreme
directions: Brown onion and bacon.
Add soup and mix.
Drain beans and put them in a casserole.
Pour mixture over beans; cover and heat thoroughly in hot oven (375°) for about 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in greased crock-pot.
Put extra cheese on top. Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1/2 can corned beef.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Form into ball.
Spread rest of corned beef around ball.

title: real old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, milk and egg.
Add in sugar.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Drain fruit; reserve 1 cup juice.
Mix 1 cup fruit juice with pudding.
Pour over fruit and stir gently.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in skillet and brown lightly. Drain good.
In a large heavy saucepot, combine this with the chili seasoning mix, soup and water. Simmer 2 hours.
Also good on spaghetti.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook ingredients (except vanilla) on medium until it starts to thicken.
Add vanilla.

title: strawberry delight
directions: When crust is cooled, mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Press on top of cooled crust.

title: pizza hut dough
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased bowl. Let rise for 1/2 hour in warm place. Knead in flour until dough is not sticky, then press into greased pan.

title: green pea salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except the peas and add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add peas and toss gently.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: swiss chicken breast
directions: Spray baking pan.
Place chicken in pan, about 1-inch apart. Top each breast with a slice of cheese.
Mix soup with wine, spoon over cheese.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle it over the soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus pesto and pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente and drain.
Add one tablespoon olive oil to hot drained spaghetti.
Place remaining oil and asparagus and all other ingredients in blender.
Blend smooth and serve over spaghetti.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, cooled margarine and all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put flour and 1/2 cup sugar in bottom of unbaked pie crust. Mix.
