Arrange peeled apples on this and cover with 1/2 cup sugar. Fill pan with mixture of milk and half and half or cream.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Start baking at 425° until crust starts browning, then reduce to 350° until apples are done and the liquid has thickened.

title: key lime cake
directions: Beat all ingredients at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a fluted
tube
pan
or
x
13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake
at
350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Frost or glaze as desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add to the liquids, 1/3 at a time.
Fold in the dates and nuts fast.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dr. pepper salad
directions: Heat one can of Dr. Pepper to boiling.
Place other can of Dr. Pepper in freezer to chill well.
Add jello to boiling Dr. Pepper and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until cream cheese is COMPLETELY dissolved.
Add cherries and cold Dr. Pepper, stir and pour into jello mold or individual dishes. Refrigerate 4 hours and top with Cool Whip.

title: hot cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain the horseradish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with sliced almonds and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
For better flavor, mix in advance and then bake just before serving.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: In mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In saucepan, heat together milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm, stirring occasionally, to melt shortening.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.

title: corn and spinach fritters
directions: Mix spinach, corn, carrots, cheese, egg whites, cornstarch and garlic.
Heat oil and drop mixture by well rounded tablespoons into oil.
Flatten gently with spatula.
Cook until crispy and brown, about 3 minutes on each side.
Garnish with parsley or chives.

title: grandma truckenmiller's strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Smooth into 8 x 8-inch greased cake pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until golden brown on top, approximately 35 minutes.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: In frying pan put sausage, onions and celery.
Saute until sausage is turning brown.
(You should have lots of grease; add some butter if you need more.)
Add garlic, parsley, mushrooms (save the liquid to put in later), salt, pepper, sage, poultry seasoning and marjoram.
Stir everything and continue sauteing until sausage is brown.
Add liquid from mushrooms and turn off the heat.
Put bread cubes in and mix lightly.
There should be enough liquid to moisten the bread.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine; line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with crumb mixture (reserve part of the crumbs).
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and lemon juice.
Beat until well-blended.
Fold into stiffly whipped Milnot.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Chill thoroughly.
(May be garnished with fruit; can be frozen.)

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Parmesan, lemon juice and dill weed.
Stir in broccoli and tuna.
Turn the tuna mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Snip four refrigerated biscuits into quarters; arrange quarters around edge of hot casserole and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes, but do not brown. Sprinkle cheese over bottom of partially baked pie shell.
Toss crab meat lightly with onion, parsley, tarragon and sherry; arrange in layer over cheese.
Beat eggs, half and half and salt lightly, but well mixed.
Pour gradually over crab mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruitcake(uncooked)
directions: Heat orange juice over low fire until hot.
Remove from fire. Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Let cool.
Mix together cracker crumbs, fruit and nuts.
Add liquid and stir until mixed good.
This will be sticky.
Line pans with wax paper.
Mash down firmly.
Keep in refrigerator.
Cuts real good after a few days.

title: easy guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients just before serving.
Serve with chips.
Can be doubled.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: pear pie-streusel topping
directions: Combine flour and sugar, then cut in butter until consistency of coarse corn meal.

title: pink and white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and cream in heavy saucepan.
Boil until soft ball forms.
Watch closely.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat by hand or with mixer until thickened.
Should be somewhat creamy.
Pour half into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Quickly add 2 drops food coloring to remaining half.
Blend well. Pour over first layer.
Cool in refrigerator.
Slice when firm. May be wrapped in wax paper if desired.

title: chocolate crinkles(cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, chocolate and granulated sugar. Beat in one egg at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into the oil mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°; lightly grease cookie sheet.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar.
Shape into balls while rolling in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until firm.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish and cover with cheese. Mix the soup and wine.
Spoon over the chicken and cheese. Sprinkle with dressing.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: russian pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and oleo. Then add liquids to dry parts. Mix well.
Fry in a pan with nonstick spray.
This makes a very thin layer pancake.
Brown it and turn. Spread with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Roll it into a tube, then enjoy!

title: mezzeti
directions: In electric skillet, cook meat and onion.
Add everything else except olives and cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Watch and stir to avoid burning.
Add grated cheese and olives; turn off heat.

title: black-eyed pea and walnut salad *
directions: Rinse, pick over peas and place in kettle.
Add the water and salt, pepper, onion stuck with cloves, garlic clove, bay leaf, thyme and parsley sprigs.
Bring to boil; simmer until peas are tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Remove the onion, garlic, bay leaf and parsley sprigs.
Drain.
Put beans in mixing bowl.
Add scallions, shallots, garlic, parsley, vinegar and oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Toss to blend well. Spread walnuts on baking sheet; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons olive oil and toast in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Salt as they come out of oven; let cool, then chop coarsely and add to salad before serving.
Serve at room temperature.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk with the juice of the lemons.
Add well drained blueberries, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: yogurt cream pie
directions: Stir yogurt and Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle sparingly with crushed walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: corn lightbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: victory garden skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef in 10-inch skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in water, rice, onion, bouillon cubes and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil; stir.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cut 4 slices of cheese into small pieces.
Stir cheese pieces, green pepper and tomato into cooked rice.
Cut remaining cheese slices into triangles.
Arrange on top.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: special chef's salad
directions: Combine ingredients (except dressing) in a bowl.
Prepare dressing.
Pour over salad ingredients.
Toss gently.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yum-yum chocolate dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: puff pastry brie
directions: Thaw pastry for 20 minutes.
Unfold and roll on lightly floured surface to a 14-inch square.
Trim to a 14-inch circle. Sprinkle bottom of pastry with 1 1/2 tablespoons brown sugar. Place unwrapped Brie on top; sprinkle remaining sugar on Brie. Fold pastry over Brie to enclose cheese.
Brush with egg and bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until puffed and golden brown.
Cool on wire rack at least 30 minutes before serving.
If too hot, Brie will be runny.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool and take off bone.
In large mixing bowl mix chicken, soup and Veg-All well.
Add cheese and mix again.
Pour mixture into deep dish pie shell.
Take remaining pie shell and put over top of pie; press down edges with fork. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until pie shell is done.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place half of the salad greens in bottom of large glass bowl. Arrange onion rings around edge of bowl.
Combine celery and green pepper in small bowl.
Layer cauliflower, peas and the celery mixture in that order over greens in bowl.
Sprinkle with bacon; cover with remaining greens.
Sprinkle with fines herbes and pepper.
Spread mayonnaise on top; sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate covered 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: granny smith pineapple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick.
Let cool.
Add chopped apples and mix together well.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning on rack to cool.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients to a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Follow cake mix directions but add the applesauce in place of water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Soak raisins in hot water until they swell.
Add raisins to mix now.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain and cool.
Add chopped vegetables, pimentos and olives.
Sprinkle McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning on this mixture and pour salad dressing over this.
Mix well and chill for about 1 hour, then serve.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix tuna, celery, cheese, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in bowl. Blend thoroughly. Split hamburger buns and butter the insides. Fill buns with tuna mixture and replace tops. Line a 9 x 13 baking dish with aluminum foil and place filled buns in dish on foil. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with chips or French fries.

title: loaf bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk; cool to lukewarm. Add sugar, salt and 2 cups flour; mix thoroughly.
Stir in softened yeast, then melted shortening.
Add remaining flour and wheat germ to form soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead until dough is smooth and satiny (about 8 minutes).
Form into smooth ball; place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled in bulk.
Punch down; let rise again. When light, punch down and divide into equal portions.
Shape each into ball.
Cover well; let rest for 5 to 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves; place in greased pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled. Bake in moderately hot oven (400° to 425°) for 45 minutes.
Yields two 1-pound loaves.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop tablespoon sized dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat well in hot shortening.
Add onions, garlic, water, catsup, salt, pepper and spices (tied in cloth bag).
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cover; simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
While softening, soak minced onion in sherry.
Mix all together and form into ball.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: In large pot, saute chicken in oil until pinkness disappears. Sprinkle paprika over chicken.
Add whole onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Cover with water for simmering and stir well.
As water cooks down, keep adding small amounts throughout cooking.
Add sour cream when chicken is almost done. Stir in sour cream slowly.
Let mixture cook over medium heat for another 15 to 20 minutes; stir often.

title: aloha bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar and add eggs; blend well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
So delicious it could be a dessert!

title: crab dip
directions: Drain most of the crabmeat before combining with cream cheese.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Top with cocktail sauce and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: elk or venison steak and gravy
directions: Slice onion and pepper in rings.
Brown lightly in oil; remove from heat and drain.
Remove all fat and connective tissues from steaks.
Pound steaks to tenderize.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Dredge steaks in flour and brown both sides in oil used for pepper and onion.
Pour off oil.
Place onion and pepper rings on top of steaks, then spread soup over all.
Add water to almost cover meat. Simmer for 2 hours, adding water as needed to keep meat nearly submerged.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small strips, 3/8 x 3-inch approximately. Marinate steak strips 10 minutes in soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and salt.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in pan; add garlic, onion and pepper and stir until tender.
Remove from pan and set aside. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in pan; add meat and stir until cooked.
Add vegetables and cook 1 minute more.
The marinade mix may be added with the meat.
Serve hot.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water; add juices and fruit. Chill.
Yield: 5 gallons.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix together.
Makes 2 punch bowls full.

title: easy fettuccine
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cream of chicken soup.
(Do not add water or milk to chicken soup.)
Add sliced mushrooms, lots of Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Stir.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles for a quick-easy meal.
Can also add cooked chopped broccoli.

title: homemade crisp coating mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Seal the bowl and shake until evenly distributed.
Pour into an airtight container that will hold minimum of 5 cups.
Label and seal.
Store in cool, dry place.
Use within 2 months.

title: open-face cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian salad dressing together.
Spread on rye bread rounds.
Top with a slice of peeled cucumber. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: coke roast
directions: Score roast.
Fill each slot with salt, pepper, garlic and celery flakes (you may sear your roast first.)
Place in a foil lined pan.
Combine Coke, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and chili sauce and pour over meat.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: winter bisque
directions: Thaw and drain frozen shrimp and spinach. Stir cream cheese and milk over medium heat in large saucepan until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until Velveeta cheese is melted.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
After chicken has marinated all day in Wish-Bone Italian dressing, roll chicken in crushed Ritz crackers. Cover and bake for one hour.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients and chill or I add Cool Whip right away.
Mix with mixer and it will be almost set when mixed together.
Good to make when limited time available.

title: banana mountain
directions: Place whipped topping in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Spoon into dessert dishes.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and heat sugar, brown sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Add orange rind.
Gradually, add orange juice, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit basket mold
directions: Stir boiling grape juice into gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes, or until dissolved.
Stir in club soda, lime juice and orange juice.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours, or until thickened.
Stir in grapes and strawberries.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold; garnish with additional fruit.
Makes 12 servings.

title: scalloped creamed potatoes
directions: Melt the butter. Add the flour and mix until smooth. Add the milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and smooth, about 5 minutes after it comes to a boil. Add the salt toward end of cooking time.
Add more milk if it becomes too thick.

title: jill's seafood fettucine alfredo
directions: In frypan, saute diced tomato, onion, garlic and green pepper. In a separate pan, cream together half and half and cheeses.
Add seafood and spices to vegie mixture.
Saute until cooked, on low, and cover.
Drain excess liquid.
Add vegetable and seafood mixture to cheese sauce.
Serve over egg noodles.
Serves 2.

title: mike's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms off with paper towel to clean.
Scoop out inside of mushroom (everything) and reserve it.
Create a hollow. Chop up insides of mushrooms; mix with bread crumbs, melted butter, 3/4 of the cut up shrimp and salt and pepper.
(A few more bread crumbs may be needed to form a solid ball.)
Form into ball and gently press into hollow of mushroom.
Place a few reserved shrimp (whole) on top of a few mushrooms.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until whole shrimp turn pink.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour.
Drop from teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, decorate with bits of candied fruit, nuts or candies.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: dakota seed bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cook rice in a medium pot of boiling salted water until very tender, about 40 minutes.
Drain.
Cool completely.
Stir warm water and honey in a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over; let stand until foamy, about 8 minutes.
Add rice, whole wheat flour, dry milk, 1/2 cup sunflower seeds, wheat germ, oil and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Gradually mix in enough bread flour to form dough.
Cover dough and let rest 15 minutes.
Turn out dough onto floured surface.

title: snickers fudge
directions: Lightly butter a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish. Mix butter, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 or 3 quart saucepan over medium heat. Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly, as mixture will scorch easily. Continue boiling for five minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add vanilla and peanuts and mix well. Pour half of candy into prepared pan and spread evenly. Unwrap caramels and melt over low heat with half and half. Pour caramel evenly over candy in pan and then spread remaining candy over top. Cool at room temperature before cutting into squares.

title: vege-cheese
directions: Soak agar in water until soft.
Boil until clear.
Take off fire.

title: chicken sweet and sour
directions: Combine all ingredients and set aside.
Broil or grill chicken 40 minutes turning once.
Brush chicken with sauce and cook for 5 minutes then turn chicken.
Brush with sauce and cook for an additional 5 minutes.

title: e-z stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers in hot water for 5 minutes and remove.
Brown beef in large frying pan.
Add onion, water, rice and stewed tomatoes.
Cook on low for 35 minutes.
Add cheese and melt in hamburg mixture.
Remove from heat; fill bell peppers with mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: new england seafood casserole
directions: Set aside 10 whole shrimp.
Cut remaining shrimp in half and set aside.
Melt butter in medium size saucepan and saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add soup, milk and mushrooms with liquid; simmer 10 minutes.
Fold in rice.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of mixture.

title: three burger bean bake
directions: Put
ground
beef
and
onions
in
skillet; cook until pinkness
disappears.
Stir in flour, salt, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in baked beans, green
beans, garbanzo beans, mustard and catsup.
Turn into 2 quart
casserole.
Add
bacon to frying pan.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Crumble
bacon
and
sprinkle over meat and beans. Sprinkle
sunflower
nuts around edge.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until casserole bubbles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Can mix night before and refrigerate.

title: french apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
For apple topping:
arrange apple slices in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Combine melted butter and lemon juice; drizzle over apples.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble ground meat on bottom of pan.
Add cheese, cut up in small pieces or grated.
Add celery soup (condensed) and place Tater Tots on top.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: twice baked potato with cheese
directions: Bake potato in oven.
When done slice potato in half.
Scoop out potato from skin.

title: dried apple pies
directions: Cut and blend Crisco, salt and flour.
Add cold water; mix. Mix warm water, yeast and sugar; add to flour mixture.
Beat and blend in eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out, using granulated sugar instead of flour.
Cut into circles; add fruit.
Bake on a greased sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh pina colada
directions: Combine everything in blender; mix until ice is crushed.
Pour into glasses.
Garnish with pieces of pineapple.
Serves 6.

title: beef ball stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Shape beef balls.
Brown in hot fat. Arrange with vegetables and salt in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: manasta(given to me this way by an old italian woman)
directions: Add to pot.
Add ladle of spaghetti sauce or small jar of sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons Romano cheese (freshly ground).
Break up spaghetti, cook and add to pot or serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Step 1:
Prepare chocolate cake with pudding mix per package directions.
Bake in sheet pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli until tender;
put in greased casserole. Combine
soup,
mayonnaise	and lemon juice.
Mix.	Cover with cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dustin's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins for 20 minutes.
Chill 30 minutes. Peel and grate.
Mix melted butter, sour cream, chives, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add mix to potatoes.
Stir well.

title: doodle-bug eggs
directions: When Jim's son, Jeremy, was 3 or 4 years old, he watched while his daddy cooked doodle-bug eggs for him.
Jim put some margarine in a frying pan and while it was melting, he took a slice of bread and folded it in half.
He took a bite from the middle, making a hole in the center of the slice, entertaining Jeremy in doing this.
He put the slice in the frying pan, broke an egg in the hole and cooked for a minute or so each side.
Jeremy was delighted with his doodle-bug egg.

title: chicken stew with tomatoes and white beans
directions: Cook chopped bacon in heavy large pot over medium-high heat until crisp. Remove with slotted spoon to paper towel. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Dredge chicken in flour. Add to drippings in pot and saut until brown, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to bowl. Add chopped onion and garlic to pot; saut 4 minutes. Add bacon, stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, red wine, basil and oregano. Bring to boil. Return chicken and any accumulated juices to pot. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Add beans. Simmer 10 minutes longer. Remove chicken. Take meat off bone and return shredded meat to pot. Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix everything, except the nuts.
Beat for 30 minutes.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle the nuts in the bottom and pour the batter over the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with Rum Cake Sauce.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Squeeze bottle while counting to twelve.
Then stir.
Then you can drink.
Make sure you put milk and chocolate away!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken.
Remove bone and skin.
Save broth.
Add soup and broth and small amount of water.
Cook spaghetti in broth and soup over low heat.
Add water, if necessary.
Saut onion, pepper and margarine.
Add Ro-Tel.
Mix together with grated cheese.

title: ronco meat & spinach manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti as package directs, drain. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large skillet brown beef and sausage, drain well. In a medium bowl, combine meat mixture and next five ingredients. Stuff manicotti with meat filling. Pour half of the pasta sauce into bottom of a 13X9-inch baking dish. Place manicotti in dish and spoon remaining sauce over manicotti. Cover and bake for 35 minutes, until hot.

title: my  surprise brownies
directions: Fill paper-lined cups 2/3 full of prepared brownie batter. Press 1 Reese's cup down in the middle of each brownie until it meets the top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish; place broccoli on bottom.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice to make sauce; pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and crumbs.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ranch style dip
directions: Insert knitting needle or skewer through center of cucumber. Using sharp knife, slice by rotating cucumber until whole cucumber has been cut.
Pull out skewer.
You now have one long spiral for garnish.

title: apricot (buttermilk) salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice to boiling and then add apricot jello and stir until dissolved. Let set to cool and thicken a little. Add buttermilk. Blend good and let set again until slightly congealed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Cover and refrigerate.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Alternate layers of meat, vegetables and rice, making sure rice is not top layer or it will be too dry.
Sprinkle salt throughout layers and the sugar on top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven, adding extra liquid as necessary to prevent excessive drying out.
I use canned tomatoes and juice.
I also have added 1 can drained whole kernel corn, chopped celery and when casserole is in the last 5 minutes of completion, I grate Cheddar cheese on top and let melt.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cut vegetables in cubes; cover with chicken stock.
Add the marjoram, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until the vegetables are cooked.
Mash the mixture with a hand potato masher or put through the blender.
Return to the saucepan and adjust seasonings.
Bring to a boil and add the cheese.
Heat just until the cheese is melted, but not thoroughly mixed into the soup.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello with Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: raisin pie
directions: Rinse and drain raisins.
Scald 2 cups of milk in top of double boiler.
Mix sugar with cornstarch.
Moisten with 1/4 cup milk.
Add egg yolks and blend thoroughly.
Pour into hot milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add raisins and butter and beat well.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and stir to blend.
Pour into baked pastry shell and top with meringue, made of egg whites plus 4 tablespoons sugar.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Dash with paprika. Place in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add wine, onion, curry powder and pepper. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken to a warm serving platter.

title: marie's meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for an hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before eating.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix margarine or butter, sugar and Crisco together, then add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well.
Add flour, salt, sweet milk and flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ham cheese savory
directions: Melt shortening.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Add ham.
Heat through.
Serve over baked potatoes, noodles or rice.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Layer hominy, chili peppers, whipping cream, sour cream and cheese, ending with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.
If too soupy, leave in oven for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: white chili
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown in oil until tender. Add onion, celery and peppers.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheeseburger pie no. 1
directions: Heat
oven
Grease
10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onions; drain.	Add butter.
Stir in salt and pepper. Spread in	plate.	Beat
milk,
baking mix and eggs smooth, 15 seconds on high speed.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center
comes
out	clean, 5 to 8 minutes.	Cool 5 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: smoky sausage 'n rice
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Saute in vegetable oil. Stir in onions and green pepper; continue to saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in water, pimiento, MBT and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in the rice and black-eyed peas. Cover; lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: kielbossi(charlie billus)
directions: Grind (coarse ground) meat (butt and ham); add seasonings.
Mix well.
Stuff in casing.
Freeze.
Cook as you do any kielbossi.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat sugar, butter and salt with mixer for 5 minutes until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until it looks like whipped cream.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add baking soda and powder; beat well.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until mixed well.
Add the nuts and mix until completely blended.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Blend butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to blended mixture.
Add nuts. Next, roll mixture into 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and store in freezer overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, put a layer of crumbs, a layer of oysters, a layer of cheese and sprinkle with red pepper.
Repeat layers. Add milk and eggs, blended together.
Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix last 4 ingredients.
Boil to dissolve sugar.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: easy chocolate cake(quick and easy)
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour in sheet cake pan.
Mix together cream cheese, egg, sugar and 1/2 c. chocolate chips.
Drop on top of cake batter and cut through with knife. Top with rest of chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Slice onion into rings. Mix broccoli, cauliflower, cheese, onion and bacon in large bowl. In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Let set for flavors to blend.

title: uncooked peanut butter squares
directions: Melt peanut butter and oleo. Add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Spread on a cookie sheet. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top of graham cracker mixture. Chill in refrigerator to cool.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown lightly floured meat in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon jello set
directions: Mix lemon jello with hot water; add juice from fruit cocktail (if not enough juice, add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid); chill until thick.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese (softened) with drained fruit cocktail.
Beat chilled, thick jello mixture until foamy, then add to cream cheese/fruit cocktail mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar, forming dough.
Press into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, building up the sides 1/2-inch.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple sauce
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Combine pineapple juice with orange juice, lemon juice, water, sugar, salt and cornstarch. Stir and cook for approximately 10 minutes.
Peel, section and slice a medium-size orange.
Add pineapple tidbits and orange bits to sauce.
Heat; keep hot.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut up onion and cabbage.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot and cook on high for about 10 minutes.
Then cover and simmer for a while longer until vegetables are tender.
Salt, pepper and herbs to taste.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour marinade over vegetable mixture and toss well. Chill at least 12 hours. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: west virginia biscuits
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Add shortening and blend well.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk.
Add to flour and mix to soft dough.
Turn on board and knead until smooth, roll out and cut into biscuits.
Brush with oil and put on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: party meat balls
directions: It is better to eat soup with someone you love, than to eat steak with someone you hate.

title: shoestring potato cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Stir in potatoes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper on cookie sheet. Cool.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Put apples in a buttered casserole.
Toss with 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar, cheese and melted margarine.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat until creamy. Gradually add eggs and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Place in oven 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
In bottom of well-greased and floured pan, put a layer of cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour a layer of batter.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: canned green beans
directions: To beans add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cover with water and boil for 20 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: yogurt soup
directions: Blend the chopped cucumbers with the yogurt and onion until smooth.
Add salt to taste and chill before serving.
Garnish with cucumber.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruits (save cherry juice).
Cut pineapple into pieces. Combine fruit and cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir in marshmallows.
(Add a little cherry juice if too dry.) Refrigerate.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions, garlic, mushrooms and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring often. Cut plum tomatoes finely and add along with tomato sauce, carrots, parsley, basil, oregano, sugar, salt, pepper and chilies.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place ground beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chopped onion over beef.
Drain green beans.
Place over onion.
Pour soup over green beans.
Add Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 13 pan. Bring to a boil the oleo, shortening, water and cocoa. Pour mixture over the sugar and flour. Add the buttermilk, vanilla, eggs and soda. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes (use toothpick test).

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend honey and butter together.
Add beaten eggs and broken pecan meats.
Pour into pie pan lined with pastry.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes or until set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it spins a long thread 6 to 8 inches.
Add peanuts and stir constantly until light golden brown. Remove from heat and add soda, butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts.
Candy will foam up.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, water and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done. Invert onto wire rack or plate to cool.
Yields 12 to 24 servings, depending on the thickness of each slice.

title: crab-stuffed jalapeno fritters
directions: Starting just below stem, cut chilies lengthwise in half, leaving stems attached.
Seed chilies.
Place chilies in heavy medium saucepan. Cover with cold water and bring to simmer. Drain. Repeat process. Dry chilies.

title: never fail dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
When browned nicely, taken out of oven.
Let cool.
Take 2/3 of this and put in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Mix pudding with milk until thick. Pur over coconut mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add reserved mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: frothy syllabub
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, wine, lemon rind and sugar; allow to stand until sugar is dissolved.
Combine milk and cream; add wine mixture gradually and beat until frothy.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add remaining sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Pour milk mixture into punch bowl, top with spoonfuls of egg white mixture sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese in microwave. Spread in bottom of large square pan (12-inch). Spread the chili over cream cheese. Grate and spread the cheese or chop the jalapeno peppers and spread over chili before using plain Monterey Jack cheese. Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot and apple salad
directions: Grate carrots fine.
Chop apple in small pieces.
Add raisins and 2 tablespoons or more of mayo or Miracle Whip.
Stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
One teaspoon lemon juice will keep apple and carrots fresh looking (optional).

title: summer beet salad
directions: Drain beets well. Add thinly-sliced onions. Add lemon juice, olive oil and black pepper. Mix well. It is best if made the day before so flavors will blend. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves 8 as a side dish.

title: easy baked fish
directions: Place fillets in greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, paprika, salt and pepper.
In saucepan, heat butter, blend in flour and add milk.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour sauce over fish.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: colonial corn bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Heat bacon drippings in black iron skillet or corn bread pan.
Pour about of drippings into corn bread mixture and mix well.
Pour into skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: crab ball
directions: Serve with crackers.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball. Chill for several hours.
Pour more cocktail sauce on top of crab ball when ready to serve.
Use as a cracker spread.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Mix beaten eggs, mustard, milk and salt.
Pour over sausage mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: irish chow mein
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add cut up pork.
When nicely browned, add soy sauce and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour, adding 1 cup of water to keep moist.
Add gravy; heat through.
Serve over rice with chow mein noodles on top.

title: slice and bake cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill 1 hour until firm.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
On wax paper, shape each part into 9 inch roll.
Cut each chilled roll into nine 1-inch slices.
Cut each slice into 4 quarters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
May refrigerate up to 1 week or freeze.

title: italian beef
directions: This can be made in oven.
I use a crock-pot.
Cook all ingredients until done.
Remove meat and slice very thin.
Strain the broth and pour back into the beef.

title: ham casserole
directions: Brown ham, onion, green pepper, garlic clove in the butter. Add tomato pulp and cook 10 minutes.
Add pepper, curry powder, mushrooms and liquid.
Cook noodles in salted water and drain. Butter baking dish and add the ingredients to cooked noodles. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke a la polita
directions: Peel the potatoes, carrots and onions.
Halve the potatoes and quarter the carrots.
Put them to boil with enough water to barely cover them.
Add the oil and seasonings.
Cook until tender; add the artichokes with some of the liquid.
The artichokes can also be halved.
Cook until heated and some of the water has been reduced. Thicken by adding the flour, diluted with a little cold water and add to the boiling pot; it should be a little sour.
You can add more liquid from the artichokes or add a little lemon juice.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4.

title: christmas punch
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Combine cranberry cocktail, pineapple and orange juices.
Chill well.
Add lemon lime juice to cranberry mixture just before serving.
Add ice ring frozen with green cherries.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring water, sugar and instant coffee to boil in saucepan. It will be dark and syrupy.
Add vanilla and vodka and mix.
Pour into decanter and serve.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: You will need 1 box toothpicks.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon onion soup mix.
Sprinkle rest over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid and distribute mushrooms over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups liquid and pour over rice.
Arrange chops on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved tablespoon onion soup mix. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar with cornstarch and tapioca.
Add fruit and mix. Fill pastry lined pie pan with fruit.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple log
directions: I use log shaped container (coffee can maybe).
Place layer pineapple and layer of Cool Whip, mayonnaise, honey and vanilla mixture.
Continue same until can is filled.
Place cherries or pecans in pineapple holes.
Make day before.
Slices are easily separated for serving.

title: kraut salad no. 1
directions: Drain kraut (save liquid).
Heat liquid to boil.
Add sugar, celery, onion, peppers and pimentos to liquid.
Pour mixture over kraut and store in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps well in glass jar with lid.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix in saucepan oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water.
Bring to a boil, then pour over flour and sugar; mix well.
Add butter, eggs, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Grease a large cookie sheet (edges, too) and pour mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour peaches (or other canned fruit) in a 9 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle cinnamon and dot with butter.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: orange-eggnog
directions: In bowl stir together eggnog, brandy, orange juice, water and allspice.
Chill.

title: true boston baked beans("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Wash beans through colander.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Add molasses and salt.
Bury pork in beans and cover with hot water. Bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours.
Add more water during baking, if necessary.

title: january jam
directions: Put the apricots and water in a small pot.
Put pot on stove and boil for 10 minutes, until apricots fall apart when stirred. Using a pot holder, remove the pot from the heat.
Stir the apricots well to break them up.
Put them into a bowl.
Add the sugar and raisins.
Stir them well.
Add the crushed pineapple. Stir again.

title: christine's doubled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Scoop out yolks and put in medium-sized bowl. Stir in salad dressing or mayonnaise to make it of spreading consistency. Add mustard; salt and pepper to taste. Fill egg halves with the yolk mixture.
Garnish lightly with paprika.

title: bacon and cheese quiche
directions: In blender, mix everything together, except bacon and Cheddar, for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell and add bacon and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: baklava
directions: Butter a jelly roll pan.
Place a fillo layer in pan and brush with butter.
Do this for about 5 layers.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Put on about 2 layers of fillo.
Repeat this for as many layers as you wish (I usually do at least 6).
Top with 6 layers of fillo leaves.
Cut into squares and then cut squares in half to form triangles.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours (or until golden brown).
Boil sugar, honey and water together in saucepan. Pour over baked Baklava.
Could also mix ground cinnamon and cloves with walnuts.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer and stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for the 13 x 9-inch pan or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Parboil sliced yellow squash and drain well.
Mix other ingredients and combine with drained squash.
Place in casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade pancake syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil, then slowly add sugar.
Heat slowly and stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Stir in flavorings. Simmer until desired consistency is attained.
Let cool.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups of syrup.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut up celery and onion into small pieces; saute in butter or oleo.
Slice up cabbage, removing the heart; boil for about 10 minutes.
Beat eggs with fork, then add bread crumbs, milk, seasonings, celery and onion.
Mix well all together; put into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top; dot with butter or oleo.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la reine soup
directions: In a heavy bottomed stockpot, combine fat from stock and margarine.
Over medium heat, melt fats and add peppers and onion; saute until half cooked.
Add flour and stir well.
Continue stirring for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add chicken stock and stir in with a whisk.
Add rice and simmer low for 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Add pimento, chicken meat, sherry and light cream. Bring back to simmer, adjust seasonings and serve.
Yields ten (8-ounce) servings.

title: corn salad
directions: *I don't use all called for.

title: golden lemon cake
directions: Combine all cake ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed until moistened, then at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 12 cup tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes, then remove cake and place on wire rack.
When cool, use a toothpick and poke holes in top of cake. Pour glaze
over top and sides of cake.
Allow to cool completely before cutting.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter and pour in 9-inch square pan.
Pour fruit including juice in pan.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Spoon dough over fruit.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: crescent delights
directions: Roll out package of crescent rolls.
Spread cream cheese on top of dough.
Spread dry beef evenly on top of cream cheese.
On top of dry beef evenly spread parsley.
On top of parsley sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Roll dough into a log and cut into pieces (approximately 1/4-inch).
Lay on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt hattie's rhubarb cream pie
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour over rhubarb. Add top pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stained-glass cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Divide dough in half, color portions of 1/2 with food colors.
Cover dough, chill 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll plain 1/2 of dough to 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board. Cut with tree, star, ball or other decorative cookie cutters. Bake on lightly greased baking sheet.
Roll colored doughs, cut out different shapes to fit on top of each plain cookie shape.
If you wish to hang them on your Christmas tree, insert a small piece of a paper drinking straw through the top of each cookie before baking.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes, until edges are golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a small amount of bacon grease; drain. Add onions, garlic powder, celery salt, salt, pepper, cayenne, beer, beef broth and enough water to cover meat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomato paste, chili powder, oregano, brown sugar and green chilies.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Cool, then add cumin when ready to serve.

title: salt cod cakes
directions: To prepare cod fish:
Soak the cod for 12 hours in enough water to cover.
Change water once.
Drain well.
Dice cod.

title: monk fish avelino
directions: Flour fish and brown on both sides.
Add water, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer about 4 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and flour until soft and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each, then add milk, orange and lemon peel and vanilla.

title: microwaved apple crisp
directions: Place apples and 3/4 cup sugar in an 8-inch square dish.
With pastry blender, mix flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, oats, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Microwave at High power (10) for 9 to 12 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add all the ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 12 minutes or to the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray pan, add rice.
Pour soup and milk over rice.
Lay cut up chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: greek stew
directions: Brown meat in butter. Arrange onions over meat. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat and onions. Cover and simmer for 3 hours. Do not stir. This can also be done in the crock pot, and it will take more than 3 hours.

title: best hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add milk, chocolate chips and powdered sugar; bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into pint jars or other containers.
Seal and refrigerate.
Heat in microwave or pan; pour over ice cream.

title: banana mandarin cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice and vanilla.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix with a spoon.
In a separate bowl, mix with a mixer the next 3 ingredients (eggs, oil and vanilla) then add to dry ingredients and mix with a
spoon. Add other ingredients one at a time, mixing with a spoon.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Bake in a greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Don't let it set over 15 minutes in pan after taking it out of the oven.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano to suit taste.
Cook spaghetti in salted water until done.
Put some spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9x13 pan.
Next layer is spaghetti.
Cover with more sauce.
Put cheese on top of sauce. Then another layer of spaghetti followed by sauce, then cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: make your own play dough
directions: Mix everything except water.
Gradually add water over medium heat; blend constantly.
When the mixture forms a ball, take the mixture out of the pan and wrap in wax paper.
Knead a few minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: banana or pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Stir in pumpkin or banana, oil and water; blend thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and baking powder.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: emma hawkins' date pudding(an old kentucky treat)
directions: Combine brown sugar, hot water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, adding just enough flour to batter to drop from a spoon.
Put syrup in baking pan. Drop batter on syrup evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato crisp
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, eggs, margarine, salt, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Melt margarine; mix with brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Mix until crumbled.
Pour potato mixture into oblong dish. Top with crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: texas bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dressing and Fritos.
Toss with dressing.
Crush 1 small bag of Fritos and spread on top before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Take pineapple-grapefruit juice out of the freezer 2 hours ahead.
Pour first 3 ingredients over frozen juice and stir.
This makes a slushy and tangy punch.

title: old fashioned rolled dumplings
directions: Put dry ingredients into large bowl and margarine and broth in center.
Stir until cool enough to knead.
Knead until smooth. Roll thin and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth.

title: febe's pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except
pecans,
and
cook to 134° (softball stage).
Add pecans.
Let
cool
and
then
beat it. Drop on waxed paper.
(If it gets
too hard, put back on stove and let it melt some.)

title: sweet pickles(made from dills.)
directions: Drain and wash dill slices in colander.
Layer pickles with sugar until all are used.
Use the jar the dills were in at purchase.
Tightly close jar and turn as often as you can see sugar.
The dills will absorb all the sugar and you will have a delicious sweet treat.

title: braised duck with black cherries
directions: Brown the duck quarters in butter.
Place the duck in a shallow pan and roast in a slow (325°) oven for 1 hour.

title: spicy cole slaw(yield: 10 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Stir well. Refrigerate (overnight if feasible).

title: grilled reuben sandwich(4 servings)
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, ketchup, horseradish, parsley and pepper. Spread this sauce on bread. Layer the corned beef and sauerkraut on 4 slices of the bread, and top with the cheese. Cover with the remaining bread and spread with 1 tablespoon of the butter. Melt the remaining 1 tablespoon butter in a large nonstick frying pan over medium heat. Add sandwiches, unbuttered side down, and fry until golden, about 5 minutes on each side.
Turn and brown the other side.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered jar.
Use 1 teaspoon per teacup for hot spiced tea.

title: chicken(1 pot cooking)
directions: In Dutch oven, layer rice, then add water.
Next put in chicken, then onion soup mix and then mushroom soup.
Do not mix. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili con queso
directions: Heat oil; add onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and green chilies; cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Reduce to low; add cheese.
Stir in jalapeno peppers.

title: sweet-sour pork sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, egg, bread crumbs and sage.
Shape into about 2 dozen 1 1/2-inch balls.
In ungreased skillet, brown balls slowly on all sides, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate no bakes
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, salt, butter and milk in a sauce pan and cook to a rolling boil, then boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir in oats and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool and dry.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon onto crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberry halves and kiwi slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and margarine to a boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas.
Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Add peach pie filling.
Drain and add fruit cocktail, pineapple and cherries. Add frozen strawberries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sandy's cornbread salad
directions: Mix bacon, tomatoes, onions, peppers, and pickle relish. Mix the pickle juice with mayonnaise and set aside. Add 2 inches of cornbread lightly packed and 1 inch of the veggie mix and top with mayo sauce. Run knife through to the bottom of the bowl so the sauce can get to the bottom. Repeat the steps until all of the ingredients are used.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend well.
Add carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oil mixture.
Blend in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and oranges well.
Add cottage cheese and stir. Pour dry jello over mixture.
Stir well.
Add
Cool Whip, mix well.
Use large mixing bowl and refrigerate.
This is a very good salad and so easy to make.

title: peanutty-cocoa bonbons
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until fluffy in large mixer bowl. Blend in confectioners sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. Cover and chill until firm enough to handle overnight, then shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on wax paper-lined trays.
Chill uncovered 3 to 4 hours.
They should feel dry to the touch before coating.

title: chicken and kraut strata
directions: Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven at 325° for 1 hour and a half.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix drained oranges and pineapple.
Add ingredients that are left.
Mix all together.
Cool and serve.

title: joni's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight. Toss in remaining ingredients just before serving. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then add horseradish to taste. Very good on meats.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream until fluffy, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with water.
Beat well.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch square or round pans, or 1 (9x 13 x 2-inch) pan, until done (about 30 minutes) at 350°.
Cool and frost with any chocolate frosting.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add pumpkin, oil and water.
Add sifted ingredients (flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: five threes
directions: Mash bananas. Add juice of oranges and lemons.
Make a syrup of sugar and water.
Add to fruit. Freeze. This freezes best in hand freezer.

title: breakfast skillet
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Mix potatoes, onion and green pepper together; fry in bacon drippings until crisp and browned.
Mix eggs and milk with salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and bacon; cover.
Cook slowly for about 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dwayne's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour real good.
Add other ingredients except egg whites and crust and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it gets real thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with egg whites, beaten.
Cook in oven at 325° until brown.
Do not burn.
You may add 1 cup chopped pecans.
It's so good!

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving. This looks pretty served in a "bowl" made from a whole red cabbage.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
(Be sure egg whites are at room temperature before using.)
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: ye ole crazy cake(chocolate sheet cake)
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in an 8 x 8-inch pan (do not grease or flour).
Make 3 holes into the dry ingredients.
In the first hole, put salad oil.
In the second put vinegar and in the third hole put vanilla.
Pour cold water over the whole mixture and blend thoroughly until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
You may then serve and frost the cake from the same pan.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour.
Stir until browned.
Put in cocoa and stir.
Add sugar.
Stir until it is melted and mixed well.
Add milk; let simmer until thick.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix together pineapple with pudding and the pineapple juice. Drain orange segments and fruit cocktail.
Blend in remaining ingredients with the whipped topping except the cherries.
Garnish with the cherries.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix until crumbly first 4 ingredients and press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and break into crumbs.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and
sugar;
set
aside.
Combine oleo, cocoa and water. Bring to a
boil.
Pour
over
sugar and flour mixture. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour on cookie sheet, greased and floured. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Beat this well; put on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix everything but chocolate chips thoroughly.
Press onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips. Spread on top of peanut butter mixture. When chocolate hardens, cut into squares.

title: mom's chili beans
directions: Cook beans in salted water (soak overnight or 1 hour in boiling water with tight lid) about 2 hours, until tender.
(Omit this step if using canned beans.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Put in casserole.
Dot top with 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 375°, stirring occasionally, for first 20 minutes.
Continue baking until thick.

title: charley in blankets
directions: Place package of frozen broccoli on a paper towel on floor of microwave oven.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain water from box and place broccoli in a small bowl.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil; add flour and stir well. Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time; mix well by hand. Grease cookie sheet and drop dough with a teaspoon for dainty fancy puffs or with a tablespoon for regular size puffs.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° and 20 minutes at 325° until golden brown.
Fill with instant vanilla pudding mixed with 8 ounces Cool Whip and 1 teaspoon vanilla or real whipped cream and strawberries.
Also may fill little puffs with a mixture of 1 can shrimp, drained and rinsed well, chopped celery, onions, Miracle Whip, salt, pepper, garlic salt and Lawry's salt to taste.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and it will thicken.
Pour in crust.
Beat egg whites
and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar together.
Brown lightly.

title: ice cream sundae pie
directions: For the crust of this pie, beat egg white with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Fold in nuts and turn into a well-buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Spread the mixture evenly over the bottom and sides of the dish but not on the rim. Bake in a 400° oven for about 12 minutes or until set.
Set aside to cool, then chill.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt, onion salt and chili powder.
Stir in pecans, coating well.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and cool on paper towels.
Store in an airtight container.

title: lemon delight pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and lemonade together good.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Put into freezer until ready to use.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings overnight with lemon juice and water mixture. Grease baking dish with melted margarine.
Brush each wing individually with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika or Lawry's seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cola and marshmallows, in a large bowl.
Blend at low speed.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed. Add cola. Blend well. By hand, stir in marshmallows.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Spread with icing.

title: easy pork and rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole; place pork chops in melted butter. Sprinkle soup mix over pork chops; add rice.
Pour enough water into casserole to cover pork chops.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A little more water may be added if needed.

title: strawberry rice
directions: Cook rice.
Cool in ice and set aside.

title: featherbed eggs(makes 4 servings)
directions: Can be prepared the day before or 6 hours before baking. Arrange bread slices in a single layer in shallow buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Combine milk and eggs, then pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Remove dish from refrigerator.
Set oven at 350°.
Place dish into cold oven.
Bake for 1 hour or until bread custard is puffy and lightly golden.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place into ovenproof dish and sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Chop carrots fine.
Mix all ingredients well.
Best when let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: very good slaw(german)
directions: Shred cabbage and onions 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Heat vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt to boil. Add oil. Return to boil, but do not boil. Pour over cabbage/onion mix. Do not stir. Cover tightly. Let sit 1 hour. Stir and chill. Use as needed. Keeps well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix. Melt 1 stick butter in baking dish. Mix all ingredients in dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Add cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream, folding it in last. Refrigerate overnight if possible, or at least several hours.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: To mashed potatoes, add cheese, sour cream, onion, & seasonings. Mix well. Spoon into 1 1/2 qt. casserole & brush with melted margarine. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven & sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Return to oven for 5-10 minutes. If top is still not brown, place under broiler only for a minute or two. Watch carefully.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baked pie shell and keep frozen until about 15 minutes before serving.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients; pour over apple mixture.
Make a hole in center; add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir and blend well.
Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; flour and brown chicken.
Cook vegetables.
Stir in vegetables, mushrooms and pea pods.
Add water and chicken bouillon if more juice is needed.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add nuts.
Serve over rice.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet with 1 teaspoon of margarine.
Melt the rest in a small pan.
Set aside.
Mix flour, cheese and spices.
Beat eggs and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in egg-milk mixture; roll in flour mixture.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with remaining coating.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake for 60 to 75 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: swirl cake(1993 cadette bake-off winner)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 (8-inch) round cake pans. Line the bottom with waxed paper cut to fit, then grease the waxed paper.

title: ham cheese logs
directions: Ripe olives are a flavor bonus.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over low heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream into mashed potatoes.
Add salt and pepper, and stir in chives.
Fold in 1/2 of butter and spread mixture in buttered 9 x 13 inch glass casserole dish. Spread remaining butter on top.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake additional 10 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Prepare tomato slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices into flour mixture.
Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Add tomato slices; cook, turning once, until golden brown.
Makes about 3 servings; 290 calories per serving.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 5 ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Use on crackers.

title: biscuit baking mix
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place or in the freezer for up to 8 months. Yield: 12 cups.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling water to cover.
With a fork in one hand and a knife in the other, keep cutting off the leaves as they become wilted.
Drain.
Trim thick center vein of each cabbage leaf.

title: 24 hour christmas salad
directions: Fold fruit into cream cheese, sugar and Miracle Whip; add whipping cream.
Can be made 24 hours ahead.
Can be cut in half.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Simmer together barbecue sauce, grape jelly, tomato paste and water. Add browned meatballs; put in 350° oven for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in a large pan.
In a heavy pan, mix sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved and boiling.
Continue boiling, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Mix well. Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat.
Pour into roasting pan.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for one hour, stirring about every 15 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and shortening until crumbly. Reserve 1/4 cup of crumbs for topping.
To the remaining crumbs, add syrup, 1 egg and baking soda, which has been dissolved in the hot water.
Mix well; batter will be thin.
Pour into pie shell and top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for additional 25 minutes.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In large saucepan, brown pork with onion, 1 tablespoon garlic and 1 tablespoon ginger.
Cook on medium-high for 15 minutes, then set aside meat mixture.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in strips, removing the seeds.
Soak 24 hours in lime and water.
Pour solution off of cucumbers and soak for 3 hours in clean water (be sure you do not pour lime down your drain).
Combine remaining ingredients and soak cucumbers overnight.
Boil for 35 minutes.
Place in canning jars and allow to set.
A hot water bath may be necessary for jars to seal.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Saute chopped onion and bell pepper.
In large pot, combine all ingredients.
Simmer for approximately 1 to 2 hours.

title: sausage in cheddar biswiches
directions: Combine cheese, corn puffs and onion.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place biscuits 1/4-inch apart on baking sheet.
Brush tops of biscuits with egg, sprinkle tops evenly with cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes or until brown.
Cook sausage patties.
Split warm biscuits in half, butter if desired, and fill with warm sausage patties.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, salt, and shortening till crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and nutmeg; mix well.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch by 1 1/2-inch round layer cake pans; top with reserved crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 coffee cakes.

title: snitz's sauerkraut
directions: Prepare barrel:
Wash and rinse barrel.
Line bottom with several layers of cabbage.
Place a large slice of rye bread over the cabbage.
Sprinkle a handful of corn kernels and about a dozen bay leaves on top of the cabbage and bread.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together over hot water.
Cool. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, then chocolate mixture.
Blend.
Add corn syrup, then flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8-inch greased pan in moderate oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Combine Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and anise in large mixing bowl.
Using electric mixer blend ingredients until well mixed.
Add cinnamon and blend in.
Beat on high setting of mixer for about 10 minutes.
Stir in orange/lemon rinds.
Fold in drained cherries.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 325° or until browned.
Cool completely and refrigerate.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Add to creamy mixture. Blend well. Stir in oats, coconut and nuts.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Mash flat on cookie sheet (greased). Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix lime juice with condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip and a few drops of coloring.
Pour into crust and chill.
Garnish with thin lime slices and whipped topping.

title: holiday chocolate butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, except the flour and cocoa.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy (2 to 3 minutes).
Gradually add flour and cocoa until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls as desired (1-inch balls) or use cookie press.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until done.

title: cheese pops
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
When mixed well, blend in flour; knead.
Form dough into a long, smooth roll 1 inch in diameter.
Cut 1/4 inch slices.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 50 appetizers.

title: stained glass window candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide in half and shape into log.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: choc-o-cherry cake
directions: Sift together in mixing bowl the flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add the butter and milk; beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 3 unbeaten eggs, the cherry juice, the melted chocolate and the sliced cherries.
Beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round layer pans, well-greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, powder, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean at 350°.
Very good.

title: chocolate `company' cake
directions: Cream butter, add 3/4 cup sugar and blend well.
Add milk. Sift flour, measure and sift with baking powder and salt and 1-1/2 Tbsp. cocoa.
Add to first mixture and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Mix white and brown sugar with 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over batter but do not mix into batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut and serve upside down with whipped cream.
