title: chicken and noodles
directions: In large skillet on medium, melt 2 tablespoons butter and cook mushrooms and carrots until tender or until liquid is evaporated. Stir occasionally.
Add cream, remaining butter, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to simmer; gradually add cheese.
Add peas and chicken.
Heat through.
Toss chicken with cooked noodles. Sprinkle with extra cheese, if you want.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut up and grind eggplant fine.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, paprika and flour to handle.
Fry as pancakes in oil.
Serve hot with jelly or honey.
They freeze well.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: Beat well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: meat balls
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Mix beef, onion, ketchup, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper together.
Shape into balls.
Place in hot skillet; turn until brown.
Cover meatballs with ketchup.
Add water.
Cover skillet; simmer for about 1 hour.

title: easy salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over fruits and other ingredients; mix and serve.
Place some orange slices on top.

title: velikonocni sekana(easter loaf)
directions: Combine all the ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°. Cut into squares.
Serve warm with celery sticks or cold with mustard.

title: jello cream cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Cool.
Slice onions and green pepper in rounds.
Mix with cooled carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours.
Drain and serve.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Serves 12.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes; then gradually add sugar and pumpkin. Mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour into a cookie sheet, well-greased and floured.
Bake only 15 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle a towel good with powdered sugar.
Flip hot cake out on towel.
Roll up and let cool.
Put in refrigerator while making filling.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in blender.
Add rotini noodles. Mix all together then let set overnight; add green peppers, red peppers, cauliflower, cucumbers, carrots, (any raw vegetable you like).

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add crumbled biscuits and raisins, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 9 servings.

title: beef stroganoff(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Toss in flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat and onions in 3 tablespoons fat.
Add tomato juice, bouillon and sugar; reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender. Blend in sour cream, mushrooms and wine.
Heat, but don't boil. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy date-nut squares(makes 8 servings)
directions: Pour the melted butter or margarine into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle evenly with 1 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and the dates.
Prepare the pudding and pie filling according to package directions.
Pour gently over crumb mixture. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Chill until firm (3 to 4 hours).
Cut in squares to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in baking pan.
In a bowl, mix together, flour, shortening, milk, baking powder, and salt, into until dough is soft.
In a saucepan, bring water and sugar to a boil.
Set aside.
Roll out dough and cut into strips.
Form strips into cups and place in baking pan.
Fill each cup with one-half peach.
Pour sugar and water mixture over cups.
Bake 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: hearty bacon-potato chowder
directions: In pot, cook bacon for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add potatoes and onions and continue cooking for 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for an additional 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no frig-cookie-cutter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cookies for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cream butter, sugar and dry pudding mix with a mixer.
Add soda and cinnamon; blend well.
Add egg, continuing to blend.
Last, add flour and continue to mix.
Dough may become too stiff to mix with mixer.
If so, continue by hand.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut out favorite cookie cutter shapes.
Makes about 2 dozen large cookies.
Decorate with sugars or frost for more fun!!
We always double to make it worth the mess!!

title: apple crisp(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash, onions and bell peppers; let set for 3 hours in ice; drain and add sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: me ma's lemon pie
directions: Cook flour, sugar, egg yolks and water in top of double boiler until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: cheese apple squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add the chopped apples.
Mix well and put in a greased square pan.
Bake at 350° until it tests done.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle sugar and chopped walnuts on top.
Cover with the sliced Cheddar cheese.
Put back in the oven long enough to finish the melting of the cheese.

title: chili beans (crock-pot)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: souper chicken
directions: Mix soup, milk and rice in a Pyrex 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cut up chicken on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Uncover and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake for 15 to 30 minutes more, until cheese and chicken is melted and browned.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mrs. george washington's crab soup
directions: Pick out the meat of the crabs which have been boiled for 30 minutes. Set aside until needed. Mash the boiled eggs to a paste with a fork and to them add the butter, flour, lemon peel and a little pepper. Bring the milk to a boil and gradually pour into the egg mixture. Place over a low heat, add the crab meat and simmer for 5 minutes. Add the cream bring back to boiling point, add the sherry, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Heat sufficiently to serve, but do not boil after the sherry has been added. Serves 10-12 people.

title: rice and onions
directions: Cook rice. Saute onions in margarine until tender. Put onions in rice. Add soy sauce to a light brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until creamy and add spices to taste.
Great to dip fresh fruit into.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, mix unbeaten egg whites, sugar, water and Karo; beat over boiling water with electric mixer for 7 minutes or until frosting stands in stiff peaks.
Remove from water; add vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Frost cake.
Garnish with coconut.

title: hot spiced cranberry juice
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 10 minutes, covered.
Remove spices and oranges.
Pour into heatproof cups and garnish with additional orange
slices
(optional).
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in bottom of a baking dish. Spoon in fruit that has been drained of its juices.
Mix dry ingredients, then add milk.
Mix well.
Pour over fruit.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: award winning chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients with the ground chuck and put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 18 hours.

title: heavenly onion casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Combine milk, soup and soy sauce and pour over cheese.
Top with bread and cheese slices.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Bake loosely covered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits, mix all except marshmallows.
Chill until serving time.
Stir in marshmallows just before serving.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Saute onions, celery and almonds in butter until lightly browned.
Mix soup, cheese and sour cream with celery mixture and asparagus.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas two step chicken picante
directions: Mix picante sauce, sugar and mustard.
Place chicken in 2 qt. shallow baking dish and pour sauce mixture over chicken.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: yakitori
directions: Make Yakitori by alternating chicken with leeks on 8-inch bamboo skewers.
Makes 24 skewers.
Cook under a broiler for 8 minutes, brushing frequently with sauce. Serve on a bed of rice with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate candy clusters
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and margarine. Boil for 3 minutes. Add chocolate chips and dissolve.
Add nuts and raisins.
Dab out onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with sugar.
Add your egg yolks, then your margarine, milk and your flavoring.
Beat your egg whites last and add.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) crusts, about 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: brandy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; roll into balls.
Sprinkle more powdered sugar on waxed paper and roll balls to coat.
Store in closed container.

title: white "hot chocolate"
directions: In a 4-quart pan mix 2 quarts milk and 1 cup white chocolate morsels until melted.
Add almond extract. Heat, but do not boil.

title: sugar grove venison stew(tastes like beef)
directions: Marinate the venison in the diet cola in the refrigerator overnight. Drain. In the morning, brown the venison in margarine in a skillet. Season with salt and pepper. Put in crockpot. Add vegetables and cook until done. Thicken the juice with flour and water. The venison taste is gone and it tastes like beef!

title: curried fruit
directions: Strain
fruit,
reserving juices and place fruit in the bottom of
a
lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan over
low
heat, combine 2 cups of the mixed reserved juices
with the cornstarch;
cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add butter,
sugar,
curry powder and cook, still stirring until sauce is about the consistency of a light cream sauce.
Pour
over fruit
and
sprinkle with pecans over all. Bake 45
minutes
to an hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Cream 3/4 of sugar and egg yolks.
Whip whites of eggs and add remaining sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa into egg yolks and sugar, which have been creamed.
Add hot water and stir. Fold in whites.
Bake in 14 x 15-inch pan, which has been lined with paper and greased.
Bake in oven at 375° until it leaves sides of pan.

title: sugar sheet cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on a prepared cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar.*
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with strawberries and pineapple.
Add sugar, marshmallows and chopped nuts, if desired.
Freeze in 9-inch square glass Pyrex.
It will freeze in 24 hours or less.
Remove 1 hour before time to serve.
Slice bananas on top and cover with Cool Whip.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Marinate the chicken and grill until light brown.
Place in saucepan with picante sauce, onions and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with cheese and continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: caulipuff
directions: Cook cauliflower until very tender and drain.
In blender, whirl together cauliflower, egg yolks, milk and salt until smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually fold in cauliflower mixture, scallions and cheese.
Spread over bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until set, 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice consomme
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion and rice.
Cook on high heat, stirring constantly, until rice is slightly browned.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add the beef broth and mushrooms. Cook, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
The last 15 minutes, uncover.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Heat tomato soup and bring to a boil.
Mix with cream cheese. Add gelatine.
Let set until slightly firm.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp.
Put in mold and let set overnight.

title: hot sausage casserole(great for brunch, lunch or dinner)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry sausage (like hamburger) until well done, browned and crumbly.
Drain; set aside.
Cook rice as directed on package; set aside.
While rice cooks, chop celery and onion.
Saute in oil, butter or sausage drippings.
Drain.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup mix and water; stir.
Add honey, soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic and ginger.
Add ribs and marinate 2 hours, turning frequently.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a greased baking dish. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk, shortening and egg.
Mix thoroughly to form soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead lightly.

title: french-style egg halves
directions: Hard boil, crack and peel eggs.
Cut in halves, lengthwise. Mix mayonnaise with mustard, onion salt, red pepper and white pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Let stand for about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all with hand.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons water and mix well. In 8-inch square pan or dish put either wax paper or foil.
Spread mixture in pan or dish.
Slice when cold.

title: fruit salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix together in a large bowl and refrigerate.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Form dough into 1-inch balls, press each ball around a kiss so kiss is completely covered.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut up vegetables; sprinkle with seasoned salt and cover with Ranch dressing.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon flavoring. Blend well. Sift dry ingredients together. Combine with raisins and pecans. Add to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: *Pam Westgaard
and
I have found this Swiss cocoa from the bulk bins
at Waremart.
We think it is wonderful!
But if you don't
have it, substitute 2 squares of unsweetened chocolate and add
it
after
you have slightly cooked the pudding mixture. Delete 2 tablespoons of butter at the end if you use squares.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: 1. Get ice cream.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine
all
but
the
last ingredient (bread crumbs). Place in a buttered 2 quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large pan and cook until noodles are done. Add rest of ingredients. Heat until hot. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rich creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in large heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Heat to boiling. Boil for 5 minutes, without stirring. Turn off heat under pan. Stir marshmallows into hot mixture until dissolved. Add 1 kind of chocolate at a time, stirring each until melted. When all of the chocolate has been added and is thoroughly blended, add 3 teaspoons vanilla and 2 cups coarsely chopped nuts, mixing well. Pour into lightly greased 10 x 15-inch pan and let stand until fudge is firm. Makes 5 pounds.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese, onions and garlic fine.
Mix together well with other ingredients.
Shape into the form of a round ball; roll in parsley and chopped nuts.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Put vegetables in mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, white vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and water in sauce and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
Mix with vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.
Real good!

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix other ingredients in a large casserole.
Add hamburger and onion and mix well.
A little salt may be added to the meat but not to the hot dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Add chow mein noodles to cover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: pleasing pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and blend on medium speed to desired consistency.

title: pork chop loaf
directions: Brown pork chops in butter and remove from pan.
Brown onion and celery in butter.
Combine in bowl bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add celery and onion.
Place chops upright in loaf pan.
Spoon dressing between chops.
Skewer together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Boil water and sugar.
Drop in apple rings and simmer.
Serve with chops.

title: glenda's pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. (Add Jell-O dry!)
Chill.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts together with onion and bay leaves. When chicken is cooked remove bone and skin, cut up and put aside. Add carrot, potato, and celery to broth.
Simmer 20 minutes. Then add noodles and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add peas, bouillon, salt, and pepper and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add cut up chicken and cook 5 more minutes.
This is very tasty and a great soup to take to a sick friend.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts together.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° and cool.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together (must be at room temperature). Spread over crust.
(May use milk to spread easily.)

title: fruited mold
directions: Coat 8 cup mold with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer fruit in mold.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine juice and gelatin, honey and 1 1/2 cups water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook juice mixture over low heat for 5 minutes until gelatin is completely dissolved, stirring constantly.
Carefully pour mixture into mold with fruit. Chill 3 hours or until firm.
To serve, run small knife around outer edge and dip mold into warm water for 5 seconds.
Cover with plate; invert.
Remove mold.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Place slice of eggplant into boiling slightly salted water in large saucepan; turn down heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Drain off water and pat slices with paper towels to dry.
Brown on both sides in large skillet coated liberally with no stick vegetable spray. Mix together tomato sauce, parsley, chopped chives or onions, parmesan cheese, garlic salt, pepper, and oregano.
Cover the bottom of shallow pan 4 x 8 or 5 x 9 baking pan with little sauce, cover with slices of eggplant and 1/3 mozzarella cheese with sauce, then eggplant.
Add mozzarella cheese, alternating layers.
Top with remaining sauce and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375 degrees for 35 minutes until very hot serves 2 to 4. You can add ground beef, browned, alternating layers.

title: smoked salmon and shrimp on open faced mini sandwiches
directions: Combine butter, horseradish and sour cream.
Spread on bread. Sprinkle onions on top.
Add salmon and shrimp.
Combine rest of ingredients except caviar.
Mix well and spoon portion onto mini sandwich.
Top with caviar.

title: lemon cloud made in three steps
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1/2 cup pecans and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until light brown.
Bake this the night before you want to use it.

title: 1992 farm and city insurance chili cookoff first place winner
directions: Brown cubed meat in cooking oil.
Add ground meat and brown. Add onion, carrot, garlic, celery and green pepper; stir until limp.
Add balance of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for at least one hour.
Bon Appetit.

title: hillary's chicken(a favorite of first lady hillary rodham clinton)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a shallow baking dish, combine butter, onion, garlic, thyme, salt, pepper, rosemary, sage, marjoram and red pepper sauce.
Add the chicken and turn to coat.
Tuck the edges under, forming a rectangular shape, about 1 1/2-inches thick.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Cook eggplant in small amount of salted water.
Drain and set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Unfold pastry crust according to package directions.
Cut out 12 circles, using 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Press circles into twelve 1 3/4 x 1-inch miniature muffin cups.
Put equal amount of cheese into each.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour or ladle into pastry-lined cups, filling each about 3/4 full.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes (without foil) until fork tender.
Cut in half. Scoop out potatoes into mixing bowl, reserve skins.
In bowl, mash potatoes, seasonings and cream cheese.
Place stuffed potatoes skins onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with paprika. Return to oven until heated through.

title: cabbage pepper slaw
directions: Combine sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Combine vinegar, mustard and mayonnaise.
Just before serving, add both mixtures to vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Combine spinach, green onions, soup and peppers in blender. Add sour cream.
Soften tortillas in hot oil.
Layer tortillas with onions and cheese, then green spinach sauce.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water together in a large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in another bowl.
Coat pecans (nuts) in egg mixture; then stir pecans in sugar and spice mixture.
Spread pecans in a buttered shallow pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken vermicelli
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from the bone and chop into bite size pieces.
Cook vermicelli, in broth from chicken until it is tender.
Saute celery and onions until clear.
Combine chicken, vermicelli, onions and celery, soup and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cold relish
directions: Grind first 6 ingredients; cover with salt.
Let stand 3 hours; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and seal.

title: green dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to hard boil.
Add jello. Cool for 20 minutes.
Whip dream whip.
Add dream whip, celery, nuts and cream cheese to jello mixture.
Cool.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Chop carrots into "pennies" and cook in salt water until tender, then drain. Mix together with mixer sugar, tomato soup, salt, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, oil, vinegar and pepper.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Next add carrots and refrigerate for 12-18 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in egg.
Add peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of the oven and sprinkle 1 bag of chocolate chips over top.

title: lemon pie
directions: Chill milk.
Beat until thick.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Keep refrigerated. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top of pies.

title: ritzy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese; mix well.
Add drained broccoli and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle on Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This may be also fixed and frozen until time to bake.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour.
Bring butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola to a boil.
Pour into flour mixture.
Stir in marshmallows, buttermilk and eggs.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until not stiff.
Stir in sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pecans and stir well until pecans are completely coated.
Spread nuts on a large baking sheet and bake at 200° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove when dry and toasty.
When cool, store in container.

title: bird chow
directions: You will need yarn, masking tape and straw.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vinegar.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add butter and salt; cool. Mix marshmallows and fruit.
Whip the cream; fold in mixture and cooled dressing.
Pour into dish.
Chill 24 hours.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff again; add rest of ingredients.
Put on baking sheet and cook in oven at 300° for 1 hour.
After it has cooked and cooled, spread with whipped cream and garnish with fresh fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Stir in eggs, flour, baking powder and soda.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix the dry cake mix and pineapple well and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake according to box directions.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Add more sugar if your taste requires.

title: banana caramel pie
directions: Cover unopened can of milk with water and boil for 3 hours on very low heat in pan with cover (this caramelizes the milk). Remove from pot and cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Spoon milk into graham cracker pie shell.
Slice banana and place on pie. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: blueberry 'n' cheese squares
directions: Roll graham crackers to fine crumbs.
In 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, combine crumbs and margarine, mixing well.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of dish.
Chill.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Spread evenly over crumbs.
Spread pie filling over cheese and chill while preparing cream.
Using chilled beaters and bowl, whip the cream and sugar until stiff.
Spread over blueberries.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green mist salad
directions: Combine pudding, pineapple and liquid and whipped topping. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix cornbread and toasted bread in stock from turkey. Be sure to use enough stock so that dressing will not be stiff. Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Stuff lightly into turkey just before roasting or pour into a greased pan and bake slowly 1 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in soured cream and put half of the batter into well-greased tube pan
and sprinkle with half of the topping.
Pour remainder of batter over the first half, then sprinkle rest of topping on cake.

title: fruited coleslaw
directions: Mix together all ingredients and stir in enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: blueberry oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl and add bran and sugar.
Stir well to combine.

title: santa bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add other ingredients.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cut while warm.
If desired, glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 4 tablespoons cream.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Cream flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together and bake in floured pans (2) for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of a large dish.
Put yellow cake mix on top, spread evenly. Pour melted margarine on top.
Mix margarine and cake a little.
Add chopped nuts and shredded coconut.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: butterscotch icing
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and salt in a pan and bring it to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk and boil 3 minutes.
Cool. Add powdered sugar and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into coconut.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brickle brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter with sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in Bits 'O Brickle.
Spread evenly in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add ground beef; cook and drain.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, add soda, salt and spices together and sift. Combine molasses, melted shortening and boiling water.
Add 2 cups flour, blend well.
Add remaining 2 cups of flour gradually,
beat well after each addition.
Let stand in cool place about 1 hour. Turn on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/4 inch thick, cut with large cookie cutter.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: cheese delights
directions: Mix all ingredients until a smooth dough is formed.
Pinch off small pieces and make into balls (size of a nickle).
Place one inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: parmesan chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart saucepan.
Place on medium heat and cook until heated through.
Serve with corn chips.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except strawberries.
Bring ingredients to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Cool completely.
Add 1 pint sliced strawberries.
(Bananas or peaches may be used, if preferred.)
Place entire mixture in previously baked and cooled pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: geneva's prairie beans
directions: Cook the sausage, garlic, onions and celery together until sausage is brown.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for at least 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
If you cook longer, you may need to add a small can of tomato sauce.

title: impossible pie (no sugar)
directions: Mix in blender for 3 minutes or until fluffy.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Place one on top of each other with paprika in between.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour sherry over top of shrimp and continue to bake 10 minutes.

title: amish country chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour with cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside. Lightly grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: cheese log
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Grate sharp cheese. Mix together.
Mix all other ingredients with cheese.
Form into log.
Roll in chili powder.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with onion crackers.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in baking dish.
Pour over crushed graham crackers.
Mix eggs, sugars, margarine and cream.
Cook until mixed well and starts to boil.
Pour over pineapple and graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat eggs with sugar, oil, sour cream and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture and blend thoroughly.
Fold in apples and nuts until well blended. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in nuts.
Chill.
Double for larger needs.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir hot spaghetti, margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs together. Put into a buttered 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Put cottage cheese over spaghetti mixture.
